1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:18,151
A makeover project
for your most unhinged leftovers.

2
00:00:18,218 --> 00:00:22,088
The best chefs in Korea will
turn your fridge inside out.

3
00:00:22,155 --> 00:00:24,157
The classy cooking show has returned.

4
00:00:24,224 --> 00:00:27,660
<i>-Chef & My Fridge!</i>
<i>-My Fridge!</i>

5
00:00:27,727 --> 00:00:28,628
-Welcome.
-Welcome.

6
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:30,330
THE 8 CHEFS

7
00:00:30,397 --> 00:00:31,631
AND…

8
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:33,600
My gosh, look who this is.

9
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:34,901
SURPRISED

10
00:00:34,968 --> 00:00:37,170
-He's back.
-He's here!

11
00:00:37,237 --> 00:00:40,607
Chef Kang-rok,
who had left us to write a book,

12
00:00:40,673 --> 00:00:44,177
has returned to <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
after a year.

13
00:00:44,244 --> 00:00:46,312
A lot has happened during that year.

14
00:00:46,946 --> 00:00:49,315
Well, I wouldn't say a lot.

15
00:00:49,382 --> 00:00:51,217
I missed this vibe of his.

16
00:00:51,284 --> 00:00:54,154
Many people wondered
how he had been doing.

17
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:55,922
He's been avoiding the media for so long,

18
00:00:55,989 --> 00:00:58,691
so some even speculated he went
to make the Tripitaka Koreana, saying,

19
00:00:58,758 --> 00:01:00,693
"Why is it taking him so long
to write a book?"

20
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:01,694
Printing woodblocks.

21
00:01:01,761 --> 00:01:03,930
-But let's not be too harsh on him today.
-Why not?

22
00:01:03,997 --> 00:01:06,232
I hear that he made a request.

23
00:01:06,299 --> 00:01:08,334
"Please treat me
like I had always been here."

24
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:09,636
THE INTROVERT'S REQUEST

25
00:01:09,702 --> 00:01:11,104
But we must mention this one.

26
00:01:11,171 --> 00:01:13,239
Let me just bring up this one thing.

27
00:01:13,306 --> 00:01:14,507
Chef Choi Kang-rok

28
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:17,577
went to compete
on the famous <i>Culinary Class Wars 2</i>

29
00:01:17,644 --> 00:01:20,346
and returns in glory!

30
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:21,581
LET US CELEBRATE

31
00:01:21,648 --> 00:01:22,549
BOWS

32
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:24,984
We're so proud.

33
00:01:25,051 --> 00:01:27,687
Will you share a word with our viewers?

34
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:30,590
Sure.

35
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:32,992
It was nice to have tried again.

36
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:37,030
The things he said on the show

37
00:01:37,097 --> 00:01:38,731
-were really moving.
-Yes.

38
00:01:38,798 --> 00:01:41,101
-You made me choke up, Kang-rok.
-That's why he's a writer.

39
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:42,635
You said such wonderful things.

40
00:01:42,702 --> 00:01:45,038
Did you plan that in your head?
Or was it improvised there?

41
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:46,973
Did you go prepared?

42
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,475
Let us stop talking about me.

43
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:50,110
FLUSTERED BY THE QUESTIONS

44
00:01:50,176 --> 00:01:52,112
-Tell us some more.
-Was our show

45
00:01:52,178 --> 00:01:54,547
helpful in your journey to victory?

46
00:01:55,815 --> 00:01:58,818
Yes, I owe 70% of it to the show.

47
00:01:58,885 --> 00:02:01,121
-What?
-That much?

48
00:02:01,855 --> 00:02:03,723
It was excellent training
for my mentality.

49
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:04,991
Yes, I knew it.

50
00:02:05,058 --> 00:02:07,694
-We have a big stake in his victory.
-We do!

51
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:10,964
-We trained his mentality.
-That's one thing we know how to train.

52
00:02:11,030 --> 00:02:12,465
That's right. We made him!

53
00:02:12,532 --> 00:02:15,034
We made Choi Kang-rok who he is today!

54
00:02:15,101 --> 00:02:17,537
Some of our chefs from the show

55
00:02:17,604 --> 00:02:20,273
participated in the second season too.

56
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:22,108
That must've been helpful too.

57
00:02:22,175 --> 00:02:24,611
That aspect makes up

58
00:02:24,677 --> 00:02:26,012
the remaining 30%.

59
00:02:26,746 --> 00:02:28,681
CHEF & MY FRIDGE IS 100% RESPONSIBLE!

60
00:02:28,748 --> 00:02:29,582
Oh, I…

61
00:02:29,649 --> 00:02:30,917
Give us 30 million won each!

62
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:32,285
This show helped you win!

63
00:02:32,352 --> 00:02:33,786
THINKING

64
00:02:33,853 --> 00:02:34,721
-Oh, yes.
-That's true.

65
00:02:34,787 --> 00:02:36,189
-Yes.
-I said too high a number.

66
00:02:36,256 --> 00:02:37,690
-What?
-It's actually a little lower.

67
00:02:37,757 --> 00:02:39,325
QUICKLY ADJUSTS THE SHARES

68
00:02:39,392 --> 00:02:40,760
-So about 20%?
-So, 20%?

69
00:02:41,728 --> 00:02:43,730
-I need to leave 10% for me.
-Just 10%?

70
00:02:43,796 --> 00:02:45,231
OWES 90% TO THIS SHOW

71
00:02:45,298 --> 00:02:47,734
The problem is Sung-jun,
who's sitting right next to him.

72
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:50,470
-He doesn't look so happy.
-Sung-jun looks a bit concerned.

73
00:02:50,537 --> 00:02:52,305
-He's always like this.
-You didn't expect him?

74
00:02:52,372 --> 00:02:53,573
I was honestly

75
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:55,408
-envious of him.
-Why?

76
00:02:55,475 --> 00:02:57,510
Even though I won the first season,

77
00:02:57,577 --> 00:02:58,945
everyone only loved second place.

78
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:02,282
So I thought, "I guess the second place
gets more popular in competitive shows."

79
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:04,651
But Chef Kang-rok was first place
and he was still popular.

80
00:03:04,717 --> 00:03:06,419
HOW SAD

81
00:03:06,486 --> 00:03:08,621
So he developed neuralgia

82
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:11,124
-and had to pierce this ear.
-This one?

83
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:13,459
Do you see that? He's wearing an earring.

84
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:15,061
WE HOPE YOUR CIRCULATION AND LIFE IMPROVE

85
00:03:15,128 --> 00:03:18,331
-You were the hidden white spoon, right?
-Yes.

86
00:03:18,398 --> 00:03:21,334
Did any of you know he'd be there?

87
00:03:22,135 --> 00:03:23,536
No one knew.

88
00:03:23,603 --> 00:03:25,772
-We didn't know each other would go.
-They all didn't know.

89
00:03:25,838 --> 00:03:27,006
We didn't know at all.

90
00:03:27,073 --> 00:03:29,909
Other chefs here had no idea
he'd be here today on <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

91
00:03:29,976 --> 00:03:31,844
-No, I didn't.
-Why didn't you tell them?

92
00:03:33,146 --> 00:03:34,214
Three days ago…

93
00:03:36,282 --> 00:03:37,283
-Hmm? What?
-Three days?

94
00:03:37,350 --> 00:03:39,619
WILL YOU ANSWER US IN 3 DAYS?

95
00:03:40,553 --> 00:03:42,589
-What now? Three days ago, and?
-Three days ago.

96
00:03:42,655 --> 00:03:43,957
I can't hold my breath any longer.

97
00:03:44,023 --> 00:03:45,858
Are we supposed to
finish the sentence for you?

98
00:03:45,925 --> 00:03:47,860
-Three days ago, dot, dot, dot.
-Three days ago.

99
00:03:47,927 --> 00:03:49,596
-And?
-Do we fill in the blank?

100
00:03:49,662 --> 00:03:51,231
Is this a test or what?

101
00:03:51,297 --> 00:03:53,266
-But I get it.
-Three days ago, this…

102
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:54,634
-We called? And you said yes?
-Yes.

103
00:03:54,701 --> 00:03:58,438
First, I heard that Chef Hyun-suk

104
00:03:58,504 --> 00:04:00,640
wasn't in good health.

105
00:04:00,707 --> 00:04:02,075
That was when I decided to come.

106
00:04:02,141 --> 00:04:03,376
DECIDED TO BE HERE FOR HYUN-SUK

107
00:04:03,443 --> 00:04:05,211
-I'm here as his rescue.
-I see.

108
00:04:05,778 --> 00:04:06,846
How sweet of him.

109
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,848
-He recently got knee surgery.
-Oh?

110
00:04:08,915 --> 00:04:11,351
I've been in pain for a long time.

111
00:04:11,417 --> 00:04:12,885
You all have no idea.

112
00:04:12,952 --> 00:04:14,487
Grandpas are often in pain.

113
00:04:14,554 --> 00:04:15,989
I put up with the pain to be here.

114
00:04:16,055 --> 00:04:17,557
-Because he was the tank boy.
-But it got worse.

115
00:04:17,624 --> 00:04:18,858
-The tank boy?
-The tank boy?

116
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:19,959
My knee had ruptured.

117
00:04:20,026 --> 00:04:22,428
He would've been good if he had
something better than barley porridge.

118
00:04:22,495 --> 00:04:24,464
I had a business trip coming up,
so I got it done.

119
00:04:24,530 --> 00:04:26,566
Did you come to the show to be my rescue?

120
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:27,667
Yes.

121
00:04:27,734 --> 00:04:28,901
MOVED

122
00:04:28,968 --> 00:04:30,770
Since you're my rescue,

123
00:04:30,837 --> 00:04:34,941
you'll cook like me,
sprinkling salt like this, right?

124
00:04:35,008 --> 00:04:35,908
ME?

125
00:04:35,975 --> 00:04:37,310
His face is about to burst again.

126
00:04:37,377 --> 00:04:38,611
FLUSHED

127
00:04:38,678 --> 00:04:40,346
-He's tortured.
-He is.

128
00:04:40,413 --> 00:04:43,483
One of our chefs, who managed
to fit in perfectly with the show,

129
00:04:43,549 --> 00:04:45,585
wants to give Kang-rok advice.

130
00:04:45,652 --> 00:04:46,786
Jong-won?

131
00:04:47,887 --> 00:04:50,323
The first time I joined the show,

132
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,858
I was having a tough time,

133
00:04:51,924 --> 00:04:53,893
but he encouraged me
with warm regards like,

134
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,895
"Let's do this together. You got this."

135
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,463
-He did?
-He did?

136
00:04:57,530 --> 00:04:58,998
-That happened?
-He really did?

137
00:04:59,065 --> 00:05:01,834
So I braced myself
and thought I'd do my best here.

138
00:05:01,901 --> 00:05:03,503
But then he disappeared soon after.

139
00:05:03,569 --> 00:05:04,637
After saying those words?

140
00:05:04,704 --> 00:05:06,973
He once let me use his lip balm.

141
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,174
SHARING WITH A KIND HEART

142
00:05:08,241 --> 00:05:09,709
<i>He said my lips looked too dry.</i>

143
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:12,078
HYDRATED BOTH HIS LIPS AND HIS HEART

144
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,880
I could see how warm-hearted he was.

145
00:05:13,946 --> 00:05:18,017
-It's so nice to have you back.
-Recently, I ran into him somewhere,

146
00:05:18,084 --> 00:05:20,420
and his lips were still chapped.

147
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:21,688
I felt bad, so…

148
00:05:21,754 --> 00:05:23,022
-Did you bring something?
-What?

149
00:05:23,089 --> 00:05:25,625
-Did you bring something?
-So I got you lip balm.

150
00:05:26,192 --> 00:05:27,727
How sweet of him.

151
00:05:27,794 --> 00:05:28,895
-That's cute.
-It looks nice.

152
00:05:28,961 --> 00:05:31,764
-Also, he left his pen behind back then.
-He did.

153
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:32,665
Did he leave it here?

154
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:34,634
I had kept it around for a year.

155
00:05:34,701 --> 00:05:35,535
KEPT KANG-ROK'S ITEM

156
00:05:35,601 --> 00:05:37,370
-The carrot shake.
-Kang-rok's item.

157
00:05:37,437 --> 00:05:39,172
<i>He holds it up when he wants to talk.</i>

158
00:05:39,238 --> 00:05:41,674
-I've been waiting for this day.
-He used it to speak up.

159
00:05:42,408 --> 00:05:43,910
REALLY GLAD TO SEE IT

160
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:48,114
Actually, the real reason
why he came back to the show today

161
00:05:48,181 --> 00:05:51,718
was because he watched the episode
when we told him to come and get his doll.

162
00:05:51,784 --> 00:05:54,687
Chef Kang-rok, you should visit the show
and pick up this plushie.

163
00:05:54,754 --> 00:05:57,090
It's this plushie.
You've seen it on TV, right?

164
00:05:57,156 --> 00:05:58,791
-They look the same.
-They're the same.

165
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,026
How does it look just like him?

166
00:06:00,093 --> 00:06:01,561
I…

167
00:06:01,627 --> 00:06:03,429
knew it was bait.

168
00:06:03,496 --> 00:06:05,365
All we did was throw the bait out there.

169
00:06:05,431 --> 00:06:06,699
A BIG CATCH

170
00:06:06,766 --> 00:06:08,968
But my daughter said,

171
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:10,336
"Daddy."

172
00:06:10,403 --> 00:06:11,337
"Just bring the doll home."

173
00:06:12,505 --> 00:06:13,439
This one?

174
00:06:13,506 --> 00:06:15,475
-She wanted this plushie?
-This one?

175
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:19,712
She didn't mind even if I lost,
but she wanted me to bring the plushie.

176
00:06:19,779 --> 00:06:21,247
HER REQUEST MADE HIM COME BACK

177
00:06:21,314 --> 00:06:23,049
It was his daughter.

178
00:06:23,116 --> 00:06:24,751
-Let's hand it over… Yes?
-Wait.

179
00:06:24,817 --> 00:06:26,886
Let's keep it until he wins.

180
00:06:26,953 --> 00:06:28,287
-Yes.
-We'll give it when he wins.

181
00:06:28,354 --> 00:06:30,156
-Let's do that. Great idea.
-Isn't that right?

182
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:31,324
-He can have it when he wins.
-Yes.

183
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,626
-It's been taken hostage.
-That's a good idea.

184
00:06:33,693 --> 00:06:34,861
We got him.

185
00:06:34,927 --> 00:06:35,895
Eek.

186
00:06:35,962 --> 00:06:37,663
I didn't expect that move.

187
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:39,065
WE GOT YOU

188
00:06:39,132 --> 00:06:40,233
I just thought of it.

189
00:06:40,299 --> 00:06:41,401
This is awesome.

190
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:43,169
We'll take this as a hostage

191
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:45,271
and give it to him when he wins a star.

192
00:06:45,338 --> 00:06:46,172
All right!

193
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:48,908
Today's guests are

194
00:06:48,975 --> 00:06:52,612
those who are as talented as our chefs.

195
00:06:52,678 --> 00:06:55,014
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

196
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:55,982
Come on out!

197
00:06:57,049 --> 00:06:58,217
I wonder who they are.

198
00:06:58,284 --> 00:07:00,353
ANTICIPATION

199
00:07:00,987 --> 00:07:02,255
Please welcome

200
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:05,258
Nana and Kyuhyun! Come on out!

201
00:07:05,324 --> 00:07:06,692
Welcome.

202
00:07:08,227 --> 00:07:10,963
-My gosh. She's so gorgeous.
-Come on in.

203
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:13,166
First, let me introduce you
the guest by my side.

204
00:07:13,232 --> 00:07:16,636
How is Nana so good at acting?

205
00:07:17,336 --> 00:07:18,905
PFFT!

206
00:07:18,971 --> 00:07:22,742
<i>She captured the screens with works</i>
<i>like </i>The Good Wife <i>and </i>Mask Girl.

207
00:07:22,809 --> 00:07:25,211
Please welcome actor Nana!

208
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:26,579
ACTOR NANA

209
00:07:26,646 --> 00:07:30,082
WELCOME TO THE SHOW

210
00:07:30,149 --> 00:07:31,918
Allow me to introduce this next guest.

211
00:07:31,984 --> 00:07:34,420
How can you be so good
at both singing and acting?

212
00:07:34,487 --> 00:07:35,822
I can't help but like Kyuhyun!

213
00:07:36,322 --> 00:07:37,990
TRYING NOT TO LAUGH

214
00:07:38,057 --> 00:07:39,392
The musical actor who always delivers

215
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,661
and member of SUPER JUNIOR,
please welcome Kyuhyun!

216
00:07:41,727 --> 00:07:43,629
-Hello, I'm Kyuhyun.
-Welcome to the show.

217
00:07:43,696 --> 00:07:45,431
ENTHUSIASTIC WELCOME

218
00:07:45,498 --> 00:07:47,533
-Goodness.
-Should I do the idol group version too?

219
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:50,269
-Sure.
-I am Super Junior.

220
00:07:50,336 --> 00:07:53,105
WOW

221
00:07:53,172 --> 00:07:56,309
Kyuhyun, I heard
you really wanted to meet our chefs.

222
00:07:56,375 --> 00:07:59,946
My entire algorithm
revolves around cooking.

223
00:08:00,012 --> 00:08:01,347
REALLY?

224
00:08:01,414 --> 00:08:03,516
So these chefs are
the real celebrities to me.

225
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:05,985
-Yeah. Oh, my.
-I see.

226
00:08:06,052 --> 00:08:07,019
Do you agree with him?

227
00:08:07,086 --> 00:08:10,523
I'm such a big fan of everyone here.

228
00:08:10,590 --> 00:08:12,058
Who did you want to meet the most?

229
00:08:12,124 --> 00:08:13,993
Actually, I honestly

230
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:16,195
-wanted to see Chef Jong-won.
-Jong-won.

231
00:08:16,262 --> 00:08:18,998
-He's the rising star.
-He's huge right now.

232
00:08:19,065 --> 00:08:20,500
He's so good-looking too.

233
00:08:20,566 --> 00:08:21,934
He's a prince.

234
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:25,071
I didn't know
Chef Kang-rok would be here today…

235
00:08:25,137 --> 00:08:26,172
SHY

236
00:08:26,239 --> 00:08:27,206
Not many knew.

237
00:08:27,273 --> 00:08:29,542
-I didn't know, either.
-Not many of us knew.

238
00:08:29,609 --> 00:08:30,877
I'm such a huge fan.

239
00:08:30,943 --> 00:08:33,513
I watched every single compilation
made on him.

240
00:08:33,579 --> 00:08:35,648
-He must like him a lot.
-I'm a big fan.

241
00:08:35,715 --> 00:08:37,750
It feels amazing to see him here.

242
00:08:37,817 --> 00:08:39,118
Look at him.

243
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:41,587
ANXIOUS

244
00:08:41,654 --> 00:08:43,523
Why don't you say hello to each other?

245
00:08:43,589 --> 00:08:45,858
-Yes, sure. Goodness.
-His ears turned red.

246
00:08:45,925 --> 00:08:47,627
RED-ROK, FLUSHED-ROK

247
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:48,761
Nana, what about you?

248
00:08:48,828 --> 00:08:50,096
In my case,

249
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,366
-it's Chef Nam-no.
-Yoon Nam-no!

250
00:08:53,432 --> 00:08:56,102
-it's Chef Nam-no.
-Yoon Nam-no!

251
00:08:56,168 --> 00:08:57,270
GULP

252
00:08:58,104 --> 00:09:00,006
-Me?
-Nam-no?

253
00:09:00,072 --> 00:09:01,908
-I can't believe it.
-Is this true?

254
00:09:01,974 --> 00:09:03,409
-I didn't expect that.
-I'm a huge fan,

255
00:09:03,476 --> 00:09:06,712
so I had watched all of the videos
and shows that you were in.

256
00:09:06,779 --> 00:09:10,082
He's very funny when he talks.

257
00:09:10,149 --> 00:09:11,551
HEHE

258
00:09:11,617 --> 00:09:13,686
Also, I'm from Chungcheong-do,

259
00:09:13,753 --> 00:09:17,123
and I sensed that
you probably are from there too.

260
00:09:17,189 --> 00:09:18,024
-She's right.
-Really?

261
00:09:18,090 --> 00:09:19,825
My family is from North Chungcheong-do.

262
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:21,160
I KNEW IT

263
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:23,796
My grandfather and grandmother
are all there, and so is my mom.

264
00:09:23,863 --> 00:09:25,731
You knew he'd be from your province.

265
00:09:25,798 --> 00:09:27,934
ALREADY FEELING CLOSE

266
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:29,268
HAHAHAHA

267
00:09:30,303 --> 00:09:31,304
He's so happy.

268
00:09:32,505 --> 00:09:35,274
THANK YOU, MOTHER

269
00:09:35,341 --> 00:09:38,377
-We're off to a great start today.
-Yes.

270
00:09:38,444 --> 00:09:41,347
Doesn't Chef Kang-rok seem like
he's from Chungcheong-do too?

271
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:42,515
-No?
-Right!

272
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:44,550
-Yes, I can feel it.
-Are you?

273
00:09:44,617 --> 00:09:46,352
-Where are you from?
-South Chungcheong-do.

274
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:47,253
-I knew it.
-See?

275
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:49,922
HIGH-FIVE

276
00:09:50,823 --> 00:09:52,124
You're from there too. Cheongju.

277
00:09:52,191 --> 00:09:53,526
-Yes, I'm from Cheongju.
-Cheongju.

278
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:55,328
I'm from Cheongju too!

279
00:09:55,394 --> 00:09:57,463
-You're from Cheongju? Nana?
-Yes!

280
00:09:57,530 --> 00:09:58,764
-My gosh!
-You're from Cheongju?

281
00:09:58,831 --> 00:10:00,499
Yes, I'm from Cheongju.

282
00:10:00,566 --> 00:10:02,501
I never knew
someone so gorgeous lived there.

283
00:10:02,568 --> 00:10:04,770
My goodness. I'm from Cheongju.

284
00:10:04,837 --> 00:10:06,272
Is anyone here from Nowon-gu?

285
00:10:06,339 --> 00:10:08,274
-I'm from Nowon-gu.
-You are?

286
00:10:08,341 --> 00:10:11,043
-Nowon-gu.
-I went to Jaehyun High.

287
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:12,878
HUGGING

288
00:10:13,379 --> 00:10:17,483
A TOUCHING MOMENT

289
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:18,684
Are you really from Nowon-gu?

290
00:10:18,751 --> 00:10:19,952
-I really am.
-Come on.

291
00:10:20,019 --> 00:10:21,087
-Really?
-I really am.

292
00:10:21,153 --> 00:10:23,356
-You aren't making it up, right?
-I'm from Nowon-gu.

293
00:10:23,422 --> 00:10:25,558
You claimed Chungcheong-do
when you made that crab dish.

294
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,860
-Yes, you made the local dish.
-I have lots of hometowns.

295
00:10:27,927 --> 00:10:29,495
Is anybody here from Jinjeop-eup?

296
00:10:29,562 --> 00:10:30,963
-Jinjeop-eup?
-Jinjeop-eup?

297
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:33,532
NO ONE HERE IS FROM AN EUP

298
00:10:33,599 --> 00:10:36,068
These two have shown
lots of love and support for our show,

299
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:38,537
and you have a special reason
for visiting us here today.

300
00:10:39,238 --> 00:10:41,440
I've been starring in

301
00:10:41,507 --> 00:10:43,676
-Death Note, <i>the musical.</i>
-Death Note?

302
00:10:43,743 --> 00:10:45,811
NOT ONLY CAN YOU HEAR
KYUHYUN'S ELEGANT VOCALS

303
00:10:45,878 --> 00:10:47,747
<i>The stage is made of LED screens,</i>

304
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:50,716
<i>-so it feels very immersive.</i>
<i>-I want to go see it.</i>

305
00:10:50,783 --> 00:10:52,118
<i>When you come and see it,</i>

306
00:10:52,184 --> 00:10:54,720
you'll realize that it has
so many aspects to enjoy.

307
00:10:54,787 --> 00:10:55,755
-I should go see it.
-Yes.

308
00:10:55,821 --> 00:10:56,989
-Is it ongoing?
-It is.

309
00:10:57,056 --> 00:10:58,824
-It'll be up until May 10th.
-May 10th.

310
00:10:58,891 --> 00:11:00,693
-I should go before then.
-Yes.

311
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:02,161
-I'll be waiting.
-Please.

312
00:11:02,228 --> 00:11:04,096
He's such an amazing singer.

313
00:11:04,797 --> 00:11:06,465
THANK YOU

314
00:11:06,532 --> 00:11:09,402
You sometimes sing on <i>Sing Again</i>,
which I watch from time to time.

315
00:11:09,468 --> 00:11:10,936
He's such a good singer.

316
00:11:11,003 --> 00:11:12,304
His voice is heavenly.

317
00:11:12,371 --> 00:11:15,274
-I'm a judge on that show.
-He doesn't sing on <i>Sing Again.</i>

318
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:16,676
He's a judge?

319
00:11:16,742 --> 00:11:18,477
BUSTED

320
00:11:18,944 --> 00:11:20,446
You just looked me up, didn't you?

321
00:11:20,513 --> 00:11:22,982
-"Kyuhyun is on <i>Sing Again?</i>"
-Yes.

322
00:11:23,049 --> 00:11:24,183
He rarely listens to music.

323
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:26,852
It's just like how you don't cook here.

324
00:11:26,919 --> 00:11:29,155
-He doesn't sing on that show.
-Wait!

325
00:11:29,221 --> 00:11:31,991
-You were a good cook on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.
-Wait!

326
00:11:32,058 --> 00:11:34,026
I clearly remember
seeing you sing on a grass lawn.

327
00:11:34,093 --> 00:11:35,795
On a lawn? Yes, that was a spin-off.

328
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:38,030
See? I knew there was a lawn.

329
00:11:38,097 --> 00:11:39,899
So you watched a single clip.

330
00:11:39,965 --> 00:11:42,068
We're sorry about that.

331
00:11:42,134 --> 00:11:44,570
I'm thankful that Jung-hwan
actually cares about me, though.

332
00:11:44,637 --> 00:11:47,039
-Right?
-But I know he's a good singer.

333
00:11:47,106 --> 00:11:51,877
He's been showing off his talent
on the stage through musicals.

334
00:11:51,944 --> 00:11:54,180
Nana, do you have anything to promote?

335
00:11:54,246 --> 00:11:57,416
I'm starring in a series called <i>Climax</i>

336
00:11:57,483 --> 00:12:01,287
with other actors like Ha Ji-won
and Ju Ji-hoon.

337
00:12:01,353 --> 00:12:03,856
It's a show about human desire.

338
00:12:03,923 --> 00:12:07,993
<i>I'm sure you'll live vicariously</i>
<i>through the characters as you watch.</i>

339
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:10,229
Please tune in and show lots of support.

340
00:12:10,296 --> 00:12:12,732
-Do look forward to her new show.
-Thank you.

341
00:12:12,798 --> 00:12:17,336
Right now,
Nana is actively working as an actor,

342
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:19,839
but she first debuted as a K-pop idol,

343
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:22,942
and she made a huge hit
as a member of Orange Caramel.

344
00:12:23,008 --> 00:12:26,445
They say she was the original crazy one
way before Chef Eun-yeong.

345
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:29,982
The original crazy one.

346
00:12:30,049 --> 00:12:31,450
You all know that song, right?

347
00:12:31,517 --> 00:12:33,552
DON'T EVEN HAVE TO ASK

348
00:12:33,619 --> 00:12:38,023
Orange Caramel was active
back in the early 2010s,

349
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:41,894
<i>but they've recently gained traction</i>
<i>once again.</i>

350
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:46,632
<i>The Orange Caramel challenge</i>
<i>has become viral on the Internet.</i>

351
00:12:46,699 --> 00:12:49,435
-Who was the crew in the back?
-Yes, who were they?

352
00:12:49,502 --> 00:12:52,037
Actually, that was the first time we met.

353
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:53,572
-What?
-Them?

354
00:12:53,639 --> 00:12:57,643
I had been watching
the challenges people were uploading,

355
00:12:57,710 --> 00:13:02,381
and those students were
the most noticeable among them.

356
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:04,583
I wanted to do it with them…

357
00:13:04,650 --> 00:13:06,719
-What an honor.
-…so I sent them a message,

358
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:08,387
-saying I wanted to meet.
-So you met up?

359
00:13:08,454 --> 00:13:09,789
To be exact, I joined them.

360
00:13:09,855 --> 00:13:11,190
SHE JOINED THE GROUP OF STUDENTS

361
00:13:11,257 --> 00:13:12,458
-You contacted them first?
-Yes.

362
00:13:12,525 --> 00:13:15,828
I said, "Can we meet up
and do the video together?"

363
00:13:15,895 --> 00:13:18,330
"I enjoyed your clip so much."

364
00:13:18,397 --> 00:13:19,832
Nana has said that

365
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:22,535
the best friend of her life

366
00:13:22,601 --> 00:13:24,170
is her mother. Is that true?

367
00:13:24,236 --> 00:13:26,672
Yes, my mom

368
00:13:26,739 --> 00:13:28,707
is such an open person,

369
00:13:28,774 --> 00:13:32,311
so to me, she's like my soulmate.

370
00:13:32,378 --> 00:13:34,847
She and her mother
are such good friends

371
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:36,248
that they go clubbing together.

372
00:13:36,315 --> 00:13:37,583
WHAT?

373
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:39,118
REALLY?

374
00:13:39,185 --> 00:13:41,921
My friends and my mom got together

375
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:43,823
and celebrated New Year's at a club.

376
00:13:43,889 --> 00:13:45,291
-Whoa.
-That's so unusual.

377
00:13:45,357 --> 00:13:48,360
How was your mother dressed?

378
00:13:48,427 --> 00:13:51,864
She put on a pair of jeans
and dressed a little younger than her age.

379
00:13:51,931 --> 00:13:54,300
-My gosh.
-She must look young for her age.

380
00:13:54,366 --> 00:13:55,935
Why do you leave your father out?

381
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:58,838
We let him join us from time to time,

382
00:13:58,904 --> 00:14:01,740
-but we need our girls' time.
-Of course.

383
00:14:01,807 --> 00:14:04,310
Your father must wonder
what the club looks like.

384
00:14:04,376 --> 00:14:07,346
He might have dressed up to go clubbing.

385
00:14:07,413 --> 00:14:09,582
-Skinny jeans.
-He could've done that.

386
00:14:09,648 --> 00:14:12,418
-He could've worn skinny jeans.
-Right?

387
00:14:12,484 --> 00:14:14,253
LET THE DAD JOIN TOO

388
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:17,423
And now, let's take a look
at Nana's fridge.

389
00:14:17,489 --> 00:14:19,358
You do live alone, right?

390
00:14:19,425 --> 00:14:21,894
Yes, I do live alone, but actually,

391
00:14:21,961 --> 00:14:25,998
I never make any food at home.

392
00:14:26,065 --> 00:14:28,234
I mostly have delivery food.

393
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:29,735
I'm feeling anxious.

394
00:14:29,802 --> 00:14:32,104
They might get whipped
with this fridge today.

395
00:14:32,171 --> 00:14:34,173
In films, some characters
only keep beverages

396
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,241
-lined up inside.
-Some do.

397
00:14:35,307 --> 00:14:38,077
-It happens often. Some are like that.
-All lined up. Many do that.

398
00:14:38,143 --> 00:14:40,112
-Like Joo Woo-jae.
-Yes.

399
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:41,714
-That wasn't even a fridge.
-I'm worried.

400
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:44,950
We present Nana's fridge,
the one she uses alone!

401
00:14:45,017 --> 00:14:47,453
-Show us!
-Please!

402
00:14:47,519 --> 00:14:49,855
WOW

403
00:14:49,922 --> 00:14:51,624
-Show us!
-Please!

404
00:14:52,524 --> 00:14:53,759
You have lots of stuff!

405
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:55,895
-That's a lot.
-It's filled.

406
00:14:55,961 --> 00:14:57,029
That's a lot.

407
00:14:57,096 --> 00:14:58,664
What? Why do you have so much food?

408
00:14:58,731 --> 00:14:59,899
-She exaggerated.
-That's a lot.

409
00:14:59,965 --> 00:15:02,668
-It's enough for a regular household.
-It is.

410
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:05,638
You said you never cook at home
and get food delivered. What are these?

411
00:15:05,704 --> 00:15:07,806
-It's my fridge…
-Yes?

412
00:15:07,873 --> 00:15:10,009
…but my mom

413
00:15:10,075 --> 00:15:12,611
likes to store up on food.

414
00:15:12,678 --> 00:15:13,579
It was her mother.

415
00:15:13,646 --> 00:15:15,547
She visits me often,

416
00:15:15,614 --> 00:15:17,950
so she keeps things that she'll eat later

417
00:15:18,017 --> 00:15:19,685
and actually eats them.

418
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:22,421
I mostly eat out.

419
00:15:22,488 --> 00:15:24,490
So that's what's going on.

420
00:15:24,556 --> 00:15:26,325
The fridge is under the daughter's name…

421
00:15:26,392 --> 00:15:28,794
But her mom is practically renting it out.

422
00:15:28,861 --> 00:15:31,664
Most mothers eat at home,
make some side dishes for her daughter,

423
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:33,933
-then come and fill the fridge up.
-Yes.

424
00:15:33,999 --> 00:15:36,869
But she comes to Nana's place to eat,
which must mean

425
00:15:37,369 --> 00:15:39,371
there's a story between her
and her husband.

426
00:15:39,972 --> 00:15:41,573
DAD IS UPSET THAT HE COULDN'T GO CLUBBING?

427
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,976
-She must eat here when there's trouble.
-That could be it.

428
00:15:44,043 --> 00:15:46,745
Yes, so she has a life at home
with her husband

429
00:15:46,812 --> 00:15:49,615
and another one with her daughter.

430
00:15:49,682 --> 00:15:50,849
I've never seen a family like this.

431
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:52,451
How much share does she have here?

432
00:15:52,518 --> 00:15:54,987
About 80% belongs to my mom.

433
00:15:55,054 --> 00:15:58,357
Do your best to spot what belongs to Nana.

434
00:15:58,424 --> 00:16:00,426
Now, the top shelf.

435
00:16:00,492 --> 00:16:03,495
These are facial masks.

436
00:16:03,562 --> 00:16:05,698
-Are these yours?
-I thought it was meat.

437
00:16:05,764 --> 00:16:07,566
I thought it was chocolate.

438
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,635
It occupies the best spot.

439
00:16:09,702 --> 00:16:10,736
Are these yours?

440
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:14,239
-They're my moms, but I use them too.
-They are?

441
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:16,608
I also use them from time to time.

442
00:16:16,675 --> 00:16:19,878
She even does face masks
when she comes to her place.

443
00:16:19,945 --> 00:16:22,614
Does she only sleep at home?

444
00:16:22,681 --> 00:16:24,917
It seems like she only sleeps back home.

445
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:25,985
I see some side dishes.

446
00:16:26,051 --> 00:16:28,988
Yes, some side dishes
are on the second shelf.

447
00:16:29,054 --> 00:16:31,090
There's water kimchi too.

448
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:32,992
And this is salted pollack roe.

449
00:16:33,058 --> 00:16:35,728
My gosh. And stir-fried kimchi.

450
00:16:35,794 --> 00:16:36,929
-That's good.
-Don't you eat it?

451
00:16:36,996 --> 00:16:38,063
At times.

452
00:16:38,130 --> 00:16:39,064
At times?

453
00:16:39,131 --> 00:16:44,103
There are times when I crave carbs
and ordinary meals,

454
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:46,672
so I ask my mom to cook for me.

455
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:48,741
Do you only eat carbs once in a while?

456
00:16:48,807 --> 00:16:51,276
I try to eat as little of it as possible.

457
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:53,278
What's your diet usually like?

458
00:16:53,345 --> 00:16:54,913
It's low carb, high fat.

459
00:16:54,980 --> 00:16:57,883
But it's mostly protein, almost 90%.

460
00:16:57,950 --> 00:16:59,084
So you rarely eat rice?

461
00:16:59,151 --> 00:17:00,853
-That's right.
-No grains?

462
00:17:00,919 --> 00:17:01,954
No flour.

463
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:04,223
So of course, she doesn't know
what side dishes she has.

464
00:17:04,289 --> 00:17:05,457
-As for bread,
-You don't need it.

465
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:07,259
I rarely crave it, but once I begin,

466
00:17:07,326 --> 00:17:09,028
-I keep going back for more.
-What's for breakfast?

467
00:17:09,094 --> 00:17:10,662
-That's why bread is scary.
-I eat…

468
00:17:10,729 --> 00:17:12,698
-You'll find something that's mine.
-Where?

469
00:17:12,765 --> 00:17:14,433
I eat butter on an empty stomach.

470
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,135
-Butter on an empty stomach?
-Butter?

471
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:17,536
I see the butter here.

472
00:17:17,603 --> 00:17:19,204
You eat butter on an empty stomach?

473
00:17:19,271 --> 00:17:21,373
-Finally, someone after my own heart.
-Doesn't it feel greasy?

474
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:22,374
When it feels greasy,

475
00:17:22,441 --> 00:17:24,877
-I put some salt on it.
-On butter?

476
00:17:24,943 --> 00:17:26,678
If we eat it as is,

477
00:17:26,745 --> 00:17:28,447
we're going to make it stink here.

478
00:17:29,515 --> 00:17:30,849
SUPPRESSED LAUGHTER

479
00:17:30,916 --> 00:17:32,684
-Chef Nam-no does that too.
-In the morning…

480
00:17:32,751 --> 00:17:34,053
-Really?
-Butter on an empty stomach

481
00:17:34,119 --> 00:17:35,421
is good for your health.

482
00:17:35,487 --> 00:17:36,922
-It is, right?
-But you haven't eaten.

483
00:17:36,989 --> 00:17:39,958
-There's a difference, though.
-It has nothing to do with your size?

484
00:17:40,025 --> 00:17:43,262
Eating butter on an empty stomach
is their only common ground.

485
00:17:43,328 --> 00:17:45,631
I guess eating that
has nothing to do with your size.

486
00:17:45,697 --> 00:17:48,300
-I'm sure you eat bread too.
-He probably eats it with bread.

487
00:17:48,367 --> 00:17:49,768
-But not ordinary butter.
-On the bread?

488
00:17:49,835 --> 00:17:51,136
You have many different types.

489
00:17:51,203 --> 00:17:52,838
-It needs to be quality ghee.
-Ghee?

490
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:54,673
-It's good.
-What's ghee?

491
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:57,409
-It's clarified butter.
-Yes.

492
00:17:57,476 --> 00:18:01,013
It only has the good fat
that's left behind.

493
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:04,083
-It helps your body regulate sugar…
-Really?

494
00:18:04,149 --> 00:18:05,584
…and it helps you maintain your weight.

495
00:18:05,651 --> 00:18:07,719
The moment fat enters your body,

496
00:18:07,786 --> 00:18:09,254
it soothes the stomach.

497
00:18:09,321 --> 00:18:10,956
-Like having a glass of milk.
-Yes, soothing.

498
00:18:11,023 --> 00:18:13,092
Do you melt it in your mouth?

499
00:18:13,158 --> 00:18:14,960
-Yes, I eat it with a spoon.
-With a spoon?

500
00:18:15,027 --> 00:18:16,862
-Like yogurt?
-With a spoon?

501
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:19,364
-She eats raw butter?
-That's new.

502
00:18:19,431 --> 00:18:21,733
It's actually better than you think.

503
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:24,036
-Is anybody here on an empty stomach?
-Anyone?

504
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:25,971
Has anyone not eaten today?

505
00:18:26,038 --> 00:18:27,172
SILENCE

506
00:18:27,239 --> 00:18:29,608
Of course, you have eaten.
No one is hungry here.

507
00:18:29,675 --> 00:18:31,110
-He's right.
-Everyone has eaten.

508
00:18:31,176 --> 00:18:33,011
-We have lots of food in the greenroom.
-We eat first.

509
00:18:33,078 --> 00:18:34,713
-May I try it?
-Would you like to?

510
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:36,148
It's so new.

511
00:18:36,215 --> 00:18:37,583
How much should he eat?

512
00:18:38,350 --> 00:18:40,652
I eat it in the morning
on an empty stomach,

513
00:18:40,719 --> 00:18:42,521
-and I have it later with salt too.
-That much?

514
00:18:42,588 --> 00:18:44,556
-You want that much?
-It melts, so…

515
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:45,958
DOESN'T FINISH HIS SENTENCE

516
00:18:46,024 --> 00:18:47,826
I'm not so familiar with butter.

517
00:18:47,893 --> 00:18:50,562
To me, butter feels less greasy
than eating a spoonful of olive oil

518
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:53,765
-every morning.
-Finally. Someone who's with me.

519
00:18:53,832 --> 00:18:54,833
FROWNING

520
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:55,734
COUGHING

521
00:18:56,502 --> 00:18:58,036
It tastes like a candle.

522
00:18:58,103 --> 00:18:59,872
-A candle?
-Right?

523
00:18:59,938 --> 00:19:01,907
-It tastes like a candle?
-Why do you eat this?

524
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:03,609
-What?
-Do you eat it for your health?

525
00:19:03,675 --> 00:19:05,177
-It's easy on your stomach.
-For that?

526
00:19:05,244 --> 00:19:07,146
It helps you go to the restroom too.

527
00:19:07,212 --> 00:19:09,214
-Does it help?
-With bowel movement.

528
00:19:09,281 --> 00:19:10,983
Butter. We're eating butter from now on.

529
00:19:11,049 --> 00:19:13,886
Many people will go out
and get butter tomorrow.

530
00:19:13,952 --> 00:19:15,087
It has to be good butter.

531
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:16,788
-I'm craving kimchi.
-Is there

532
00:19:16,855 --> 00:19:19,458
any particular dish you love
that you can share with us?

533
00:19:19,525 --> 00:19:20,893
At times, my mom makes

534
00:19:20,959 --> 00:19:22,895
-my favorite dish, kimchi<i>-jjigae.</i>
-Kimchi stew.

535
00:19:22,961 --> 00:19:25,264
-I also like pasta.
-Pasta.

536
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:27,399
Also, pizza with lots of toppings.

537
00:19:27,466 --> 00:19:29,067
Like Chicago pizza?

538
00:19:29,134 --> 00:19:30,469
Yes, Chicago pizza.

539
00:19:30,536 --> 00:19:32,671
-I like it with lots of cheese.
-But you stay on a diet.

540
00:19:32,738 --> 00:19:35,073
-She restrains herself to keep her shape.
-Right?

541
00:19:35,140 --> 00:19:36,441
Peanut butter.

542
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:39,311
-Yes, I heard it's good for you.
-Is this…

543
00:19:39,378 --> 00:19:40,512
Do you also eat it with a spoon

544
00:19:40,579 --> 00:19:41,847
-because it's good for you?
-Yes.

545
00:19:41,914 --> 00:19:44,650
I like to dip apples in it.

546
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,685
That's a good brand.

547
00:19:46,752 --> 00:19:48,620
But doesn't it include that?

548
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:51,490
-It has a bit of sugar.
-Right? My mom got that.

549
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:55,794
-This is…
-They're about the same age, so…

550
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:58,630
-This one is Nana's.
-The one made with 100% peanuts.

551
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,666
-And this one is your mom's.
-Yes.

552
00:20:00,732 --> 00:20:02,734
Did you hear soy milk is good for you too?

553
00:20:02,801 --> 00:20:03,869
That's right.

554
00:20:03,936 --> 00:20:06,271
-I get everything people say is healthy.
-I see.

555
00:20:06,338 --> 00:20:07,706
-Another shelf down.
-Veggies.

556
00:20:07,773 --> 00:20:09,608
Veggies. Radish, perilla leaves,

557
00:20:09,675 --> 00:20:12,978
-mushroom, carrots, bok choy.
-Bok choy.

558
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:14,413
Do you eat all these?

559
00:20:14,479 --> 00:20:16,181
I do eat everything,

560
00:20:16,248 --> 00:20:18,283
but I rarely eat carrots.

561
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:20,319
-Many people don't.
-She doesn't like carrots.

562
00:20:20,385 --> 00:20:22,754
-I really love radishes.
-You do?

563
00:20:22,821 --> 00:20:25,224
-How do you eat it?
-I usually…

564
00:20:26,091 --> 00:20:26,925
Like this?

565
00:20:27,859 --> 00:20:29,528
You've been around for a long time too.

566
00:20:29,595 --> 00:20:31,163
He's getting old too.

567
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:32,331
The radish grinder.

568
00:20:32,397 --> 00:20:34,499
I like to add radish
to spicy braised chicken

569
00:20:34,566 --> 00:20:37,102
-instead of potatoes.
-It sounds refreshing.

570
00:20:37,669 --> 00:20:39,438
It sounds refreshing and delicious.

571
00:20:39,504 --> 00:20:41,373
Let's check out the freezer.

572
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:43,475
Strip loin. She has lots of nice cuts.

573
00:20:43,542 --> 00:20:46,612
Strip loin. Many different cuts. Sirloin.

574
00:20:46,678 --> 00:20:48,814
Do you have a favorite cut?

575
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:50,382
I like all meat,

576
00:20:50,449 --> 00:20:52,918
but I like the parts
that people call miscellaneous cuts.

577
00:20:52,985 --> 00:20:54,286
-Pork neck.
-Miscellaneous cuts.

578
00:20:54,353 --> 00:20:56,521
-I like those odd cuts.
-They're good.

579
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:58,457
She has lots of seafood here too.

580
00:20:58,523 --> 00:21:01,693
There's a lot, starting with scallops.

581
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,428
-Abalone.
-Squid.

582
00:21:03,495 --> 00:21:04,930
-Lots of abalones.
-She has everything.

583
00:21:04,997 --> 00:21:07,833
-I do like seafood, but…
-You have a lot.

584
00:21:07,899 --> 00:21:09,268
I do like it,

585
00:21:09,334 --> 00:21:10,902
-but I've never seen those.
-You haven't?

586
00:21:10,969 --> 00:21:12,070
-Gosh.
-She likes it,

587
00:21:12,137 --> 00:21:14,273
-but she didn't know she had so much.
-Courtesy of her mother.

588
00:21:14,339 --> 00:21:16,875
Aren't we so glad
her mother filled up her fridge?

589
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:18,744
She wouldn't have had anything.

590
00:21:18,810 --> 00:21:19,678
Goodness.

591
00:21:19,745 --> 00:21:21,647
Why do you have so many bags of dim sum?

592
00:21:21,713 --> 00:21:22,948
-My mom likes it.
-Is it her mother's?

593
00:21:23,015 --> 00:21:24,349
-It's her mom's.
-Is it your mom's?

594
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:25,651
Must've been on a shopping channel.

595
00:21:25,717 --> 00:21:27,286
What about this pizza?

596
00:21:27,352 --> 00:21:29,454
That's my mom's.

597
00:21:29,521 --> 00:21:30,656
And the breads too?

598
00:21:30,722 --> 00:21:32,190
-Yes, those are hers too.
-Wow.

599
00:21:32,257 --> 00:21:34,459
-And the ice cream?
-That's hers too.

600
00:21:34,526 --> 00:21:36,395
-These are all her mom's.
-Has she started…

601
00:21:36,461 --> 00:21:39,731
-She eats well. She's not fussy.
-…a new life at your place?

602
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:42,401
Does your mom want to live alone?

603
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:44,770
Yes, we're looking at your mom's food.

604
00:21:44,836 --> 00:21:46,271
What's this?

605
00:21:46,338 --> 00:21:47,673
Is it frozen?

606
00:21:47,739 --> 00:21:49,574
-I don't know.
-Delivery food?

607
00:21:49,641 --> 00:21:53,178
The production crew knows.
It's the kimchi<i>-jjigae</i> her mom made.

608
00:21:53,245 --> 00:21:56,281
-It's for an emergency.
-An emergency stew.

609
00:21:56,348 --> 00:21:58,884
I've never seen kimchi<i>-jjigae</i>
made for an emergency.

610
00:21:58,950 --> 00:22:01,853
-When they have nothing to eat.
-You sometimes want it so suddenly.

611
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:02,754
Kimchi<i>-jjigae.</i>

612
00:22:02,821 --> 00:22:05,490
Are these nuts? No, tea.

613
00:22:05,557 --> 00:22:06,858
Toppings for date tea.

614
00:22:06,925 --> 00:22:08,827
She must make <i>ssanghwacha</i>,
medicinal herb tea.

615
00:22:08,894 --> 00:22:11,496
She must make
<i>ssanghwacha</i> for you at home.

616
00:22:11,563 --> 00:22:13,765
-This is…
-See? It has dates.

617
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:16,702
If she leaves her tea here,
it must mean she pretty much…

618
00:22:16,768 --> 00:22:18,537
-There it is.
-See?

619
00:22:18,603 --> 00:22:21,907
These are toppings for <i>ssanghwacha</i>.
Dates and pine nuts.

620
00:22:21,973 --> 00:22:24,843
Doesn't it look like it's her father
who moved out of their home?

621
00:22:24,910 --> 00:22:27,979
-Think about it.
-She left her tea without telling Nana.

622
00:22:28,046 --> 00:22:30,248
Her mother was at home
when we went to her place

623
00:22:30,315 --> 00:22:32,484
-to get the fridge.
-You're right.

624
00:22:32,551 --> 00:22:34,486
And she said something like,

625
00:22:34,553 --> 00:22:37,456
"What am I going to eat?
You're taking my emergency food."

626
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:40,158
-Should've left the kimchi<i>-jjigae</i> there.
-Right?

627
00:22:40,225 --> 00:22:42,928
Anyway, that's all for Nana's fridge.

628
00:22:42,994 --> 00:22:44,162
DONE CHECKING HER FRIDGE

629
00:22:44,229 --> 00:22:45,297
My goodness.

630
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:47,799
We owe it all to your mother.

631
00:22:47,866 --> 00:22:50,469
And now, let's find out her orders.

632
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:52,104
What is she looking for?

633
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:53,805
Who Wants a No-Carb High-Fat Dish?

634
00:22:53,872 --> 00:22:56,341
-Nana!
-Nana!

635
00:22:56,408 --> 00:22:57,542
EVERYONE COPIES HER

636
00:22:57,609 --> 00:23:00,212
Who Wants a No-Carb High-Fat Dish?

637
00:23:00,278 --> 00:23:03,081
I want you to make something
that has zero carbs.

638
00:23:03,148 --> 00:23:04,950
-Not just low-carbs.
-Yes, these chefs

639
00:23:05,016 --> 00:23:06,518
-are all very talented.
-No carbs.

640
00:23:06,585 --> 00:23:07,786
-So no carbs.
-Yes.

641
00:23:07,853 --> 00:23:08,854
That's great.

642
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,756
I'd like you to make me

643
00:23:10,822 --> 00:23:13,024
-a delicious no-carb high-fat dish.
-That sounds so hard.

644
00:23:13,091 --> 00:23:14,559
I'll be able to enjoy it happily.

645
00:23:14,626 --> 00:23:15,927
A delicious no-carb high-fat dish.

646
00:23:15,994 --> 00:23:17,729
What's the next order?

647
00:23:17,796 --> 00:23:18,663
The second one.

648
00:23:19,297 --> 00:23:21,032
Who Wants to Delete Mom's Ingredients?

649
00:23:21,099 --> 00:23:23,602
-Me, Me!
-Me, Me!

650
00:23:23,668 --> 00:23:26,805
"Who Wants to Delete Mom's Ingredients?"
I think I get it.

651
00:23:26,872 --> 00:23:29,608
She takes up a huge share of my fridge,

652
00:23:29,674 --> 00:23:34,112
so please use as many of her ingredients
as you possibly can

653
00:23:34,179 --> 00:23:36,948
-and make me something delicious.
-Okay.

654
00:23:37,015 --> 00:23:40,852
You already mentioned
that you felt like you were already close

655
00:23:40,919 --> 00:23:42,888
-to Chef Nam-no.
-Nana!

656
00:23:42,954 --> 00:23:46,792
-Also, he doesn't have any stars.
-He doesn't.

657
00:23:46,858 --> 00:23:49,094
-He doesn't?
-General No-Stars.

658
00:23:49,161 --> 00:23:51,763
-General No-Stars.
-We've been calling him General No-Stars.

659
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:54,199
General No-Stars, Chef Nam-no.

660
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:56,034
-You get a chance first.
-Nana!

661
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:57,803
I'll make a no-carb high-fat dish.

662
00:23:57,869 --> 00:23:59,438
-Why?
-Really?

663
00:23:59,504 --> 00:24:01,673
I always use loads of butter,

664
00:24:02,340 --> 00:24:03,708
so it's perfect for me.

665
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:06,711
-He probably won already.
-He's famous for using lots of butter.

666
00:24:06,778 --> 00:24:08,580
May I pick my opponent?

667
00:24:08,647 --> 00:24:09,881
Your opponent?

668
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:11,516
-What?
-Do you want to fight someone?

669
00:24:11,583 --> 00:24:12,417
I have no stars,

670
00:24:12,484 --> 00:24:14,786
-so I want to fight Chef Eun-yeong.
-Chef Eun-yeong?

671
00:24:14,853 --> 00:24:16,955
-Why? I have many stars.
-Chef Eun-yeong?

672
00:24:17,022 --> 00:24:18,557
She's been on a roll lately.

673
00:24:18,623 --> 00:24:19,591
She's on fire.

674
00:24:19,658 --> 00:24:23,662
She's a chef in Chinese cuisine,
so if she can't use noodles, rice,

675
00:24:23,728 --> 00:24:26,364
-And starch.
-frying batter, or even starch,

676
00:24:26,431 --> 00:24:28,333
-she can't do much.
-She can't make a thing.

677
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,335
-Yes.
-She's all tied up.

678
00:24:30,402 --> 00:24:31,770
That's fatal in Chinese food.

679
00:24:31,837 --> 00:24:34,339
-She'd be incomplete.
-Nam-no challenges her.

680
00:24:34,406 --> 00:24:36,675
-A strategic move.
-That's right.

681
00:24:36,741 --> 00:24:40,245
Okay, I'll also join
Who Wants a No-Carb High-Fat Dish? Nana!

682
00:24:40,312 --> 00:24:41,413
-Are you in?
-Yes.

683
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:44,616
-She's the no-carb, he's the high-fat.
-High-fat?

684
00:24:44,683 --> 00:24:46,318
Oh, they're split?

685
00:24:46,384 --> 00:24:48,119
-No-carb, high-fat.
-No-carb, high-fat.

686
00:24:48,186 --> 00:24:49,855
Yoon Nam-no versus Park Eun-yeong.

687
00:24:49,921 --> 00:24:54,159
Next, who wants to cook
with Nana's mother's ingredients?

688
00:24:54,226 --> 00:24:55,660
Me, me!

689
00:24:55,727 --> 00:24:57,295
-"Me, me!"
-I'm in.

690
00:24:57,362 --> 00:24:59,097
SAM KIM WILL DELETE THEM

691
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:00,732
Hey, Sam.

692
00:25:00,799 --> 00:25:03,101
She has lots of seafood and meat,

693
00:25:03,168 --> 00:25:04,836
and I'm sure I can use up lots of them.

694
00:25:04,903 --> 00:25:06,571
-Please do that.
-He's so cool.

695
00:25:06,638 --> 00:25:07,739
She has lots of ingredients.

696
00:25:07,806 --> 00:25:09,941
Who Wants to Delete Mom's Ingredients?

697
00:25:10,008 --> 00:25:11,710
-Me, me?
-What?

698
00:25:11,776 --> 00:25:13,211
-Sung-jun?
-What?

699
00:25:13,278 --> 00:25:15,647
As Nana's big fan,

700
00:25:15,714 --> 00:25:18,383
-He changed his stan again.
-I should cook for her.

701
00:25:18,450 --> 00:25:20,886
I'd like to cook for Nana today.

702
00:25:20,952 --> 00:25:23,655
-Sung-jun joins the round against Sam.
-Yes.

703
00:25:23,722 --> 00:25:27,492
Then first, Chef Yoon Nam-no
and Chef Park Eun-yeong

704
00:25:27,559 --> 00:25:30,762
will fight against each other
and make no-carb, high-fat dishes!

705
00:25:30,829 --> 00:25:33,398
Nana!

706
00:25:33,465 --> 00:25:37,836
<i>We're about to begin the first round</i>
<i>played with Nana's ingredients.</i>

707
00:25:37,903 --> 00:25:40,605
The one with crazy eyes,
Chef Park Eun-yeong,

708
00:25:40,672 --> 00:25:42,474
versus the one with a crazy appetite,

709
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:45,176
Chef Yoon Nam-no.

710
00:25:45,243 --> 00:25:47,512
Here's one problem for Chef Nam-no.

711
00:25:47,579 --> 00:25:49,114
We're now nearing the end of March,

712
00:25:49,180 --> 00:25:51,850
and he has yet to win a star…

713
00:25:51,917 --> 00:25:54,252
-Why don't you have one?
-…in this new season.

714
00:25:54,319 --> 00:25:57,088
Did you think Chef Eun-yeong
would be disadvantaged

715
00:25:57,155 --> 00:25:59,824
-if she tried to fill this order?
-Yes.

716
00:25:59,891 --> 00:26:02,694
It may seem like I'm cheating,

717
00:26:02,761 --> 00:26:04,195
but I have to save myself first.

718
00:26:04,262 --> 00:26:05,897
-I have no stars.
-He's in a hurry.

719
00:26:05,964 --> 00:26:07,732
You have to go after her.
That's how it is.

720
00:26:07,799 --> 00:26:10,268
He wants to sacrifice Chef Eun-yeong
and take his first star.

721
00:26:10,335 --> 00:26:13,071
Actually, what he said is true.

722
00:26:13,138 --> 00:26:14,639
It may seem disadvantageous,

723
00:26:14,706 --> 00:26:17,576
but I can still win against him
even without using carbs.

724
00:26:17,642 --> 00:26:19,010
That's why I joined the fight.

725
00:26:19,077 --> 00:26:20,478
SO COOL OF HER

726
00:26:20,545 --> 00:26:24,349
I thought of the reason
why he hasn't won any stars yet.

727
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:27,619
He's here to cook for a guest,
so he should cook to their appetite.

728
00:26:27,686 --> 00:26:30,155
But I think he only comes here to eat.

729
00:26:30,221 --> 00:26:31,790
ONLY COMES WITH THE INTENTION TO EAT

730
00:26:31,856 --> 00:26:33,258
That's why

731
00:26:33,325 --> 00:26:36,328
I wonder if he even understands
the gist behind the order.

732
00:26:36,394 --> 00:26:38,163
Does he understand the order?

733
00:26:38,229 --> 00:26:40,732
Are you aware of this order?
It's no-carb, high-fat.

734
00:26:40,799 --> 00:26:43,301
-No-carb, high-fat.
-Yes.

