PERILLA LEAVES

1209
00:43:02,813 --> 00:43:03,881
-Sesame.
-Four.

1210
00:43:03,948 --> 00:43:05,883
-Sesame.
-Ring the bell first.

1211
00:43:05,950 --> 00:43:07,251
-Two.
-Nam-no, ring the bell first.

1212
00:43:07,318 --> 00:43:09,153
-Wrap up and ring the bell.
-Nam-no, ring it first.

1213
00:43:09,219 --> 00:43:10,688
Nam-no is done.

1214
00:43:10,754 --> 00:43:13,190
Eun-yeong pulls out
the lasagna from the oven.

1215
00:43:13,257 --> 00:43:16,260
-I think I had this in southern Italy.
-It looks pretty.

1216
00:43:16,327 --> 00:43:17,628
It looks pretty.

1217
00:43:17,695 --> 00:43:18,996
-What?
-Ring the bell.

1218
00:43:19,063 --> 00:43:20,364
Chef Eun-yeong finishes too.

1219
00:43:20,431 --> 00:43:23,067
-It looks pretty.
-That <i>Mapo </i>tofu looks good.

1220
00:43:23,133 --> 00:43:25,736
They really did it in just 15 minutes.

1221
00:43:25,803 --> 00:43:27,371
It smells like cold cucumber salad.

1222
00:43:29,139 --> 00:43:31,375
-Is that smashed cucumber salad?
-It's a Chinese salad.

1223
00:43:31,442 --> 00:43:32,810
CRUNCH

1224
00:43:32,876 --> 00:43:34,278
It does taste like smashed cucumber salad.

1225
00:43:34,878 --> 00:43:36,380
I told you. That's what it is.

1226
00:43:36,447 --> 00:43:38,248
I used Oriental dressing.

1227
00:43:38,315 --> 00:43:39,383
Smashed apple salad.

1228
00:43:39,450 --> 00:43:41,752
-Good work today, Nam-no.
-Good job.

1229
00:43:41,819 --> 00:43:42,953
WHO WANTS NO-CARB HIGH-FAT FOOD?

1230
00:43:43,020 --> 00:43:45,889
ME, ME

1231
00:43:46,357 --> 00:43:48,359
THEY DON'T LOOK LIKE
NO-CARB HIGH-FAT DISHES

1232
00:43:48,425 --> 00:43:50,094
They both look stunning.

1233
00:43:50,160 --> 00:43:54,331
And now, both chefs have finished making
no-carb, high-fat dishes for Nana.

1234
00:43:54,398 --> 00:43:55,799
A BRIGHT SMILE

1235
00:43:55,866 --> 00:43:57,468
You seem happy. Are you pleased?

1236
00:43:57,534 --> 00:43:59,670
I'm absolutely astonished

1237
00:43:59,737 --> 00:44:01,905
-that they made these within that time.
-Yes.

1238
00:44:01,972 --> 00:44:03,574
-My gosh.
-They're so cool.

1239
00:44:03,641 --> 00:44:04,942
Aren't they?

1240
00:44:05,009 --> 00:44:06,944
-You look stunned too, Kyuhyun.
-Actually,

1241
00:44:07,011 --> 00:44:11,415
I always thought, "15 minutes?
They probably get a little more."

1242
00:44:11,482 --> 00:44:14,151
-But they really did it in 15 minutes.
-They did.

1243
00:44:14,218 --> 00:44:16,420
Chef Nam-no did his best,

1244
00:44:16,487 --> 00:44:19,023
and Chef Eun-yeong… Yes…

1245
00:44:19,089 --> 00:44:22,059
LOOKING CALM EVEN AFTER THE URGENT BATTLE

1246
00:44:22,126 --> 00:44:24,795
I love how she always has
such a confident look on her face.

1247
00:44:25,195 --> 00:44:27,464
SHAMELESS

1248
00:44:27,531 --> 00:44:29,466
She became rather brazen.

1249
00:44:29,533 --> 00:44:32,970
First, please try Chef Nam-no's dish.

1250
00:44:33,037 --> 00:44:34,038
<i>Yoon Nam-No Carbs.</i>

1251
00:44:34,104 --> 00:44:35,105
FULL OF BUTTERY AROMA!

1252
00:44:35,172 --> 00:44:37,508
TTEOKGALBI WITH ABALONE

1253
00:44:38,709 --> 00:44:40,210
FULL OF VIBES!

1254
00:44:40,277 --> 00:44:42,046
SALTED POLLACK ROE AND AVOCADO MOUSSE

1255
00:44:42,946 --> 00:44:46,183
CHEF YOON NAM-NO'S YOON NAM-NO CARBS

1256
00:44:46,250 --> 00:44:47,384
Before she eats,

1257
00:44:47,451 --> 00:44:49,219
I have something to ask Eun-yeong.

1258
00:44:49,286 --> 00:44:50,854
-Yes?
-May I add some lemon zest?

1259
00:44:50,921 --> 00:44:51,889
NODS

1260
00:44:51,955 --> 00:44:53,624
-What's with that face?
-I know my dish is good,

1261
00:44:53,691 --> 00:44:55,259
so adding that won't change anything.

1262
00:44:55,325 --> 00:44:56,694
She's such a tough woman.

1263
00:44:56,760 --> 00:44:59,129
LIVE LIFE JUST LIKE EUN-YEONG!

1264
00:44:59,196 --> 00:45:01,265
MAKES A VISIT HIMSELF

1265
00:45:01,331 --> 00:45:03,867
TO ADD A GENEROUS AMOUNT OF LEMON ZEST

1266
00:45:03,934 --> 00:45:06,170
He's desperate to win.

1267
00:45:06,236 --> 00:45:07,905
-What should she begin with?
-Yes.

1268
00:45:07,971 --> 00:45:11,041
First, dip a piece of apple
in the avocado mousse and try that.

1269
00:45:11,108 --> 00:45:13,777
Then, dig all the way in
and get some salted pollack roe too.

1270
00:45:14,178 --> 00:45:15,612
AMAZED

1271
00:45:15,679 --> 00:45:17,915
-Let me just put the pit aside.
-Yes.

1272
00:45:17,981 --> 00:45:19,817
-Do that.
-She removes the pit.

1273
00:45:19,883 --> 00:45:21,952
She'll remove it anyway,
so why did he put it there?

1274
00:45:22,853 --> 00:45:24,555
-It's the vibe.
-It's for the vibe.

1275
00:45:24,621 --> 00:45:26,790
Just the mousse on the apple.

1276
00:45:26,857 --> 00:45:28,025
I wonder what it's like.

1277
00:45:29,493 --> 00:45:30,461
Does it taste healthy?

1278
00:45:30,527 --> 00:45:33,197
She usually eats apples
with peanut butter.

1279
00:45:33,263 --> 00:45:34,164
WHAT'S IT LIKE?

1280
00:45:34,231 --> 00:45:36,166
How's the avocado mousse?

1281
00:45:36,233 --> 00:45:37,701
-The apple…
-She doesn't seem sure.

1282
00:45:37,768 --> 00:45:39,470
It's the first time

1283
00:45:39,536 --> 00:45:41,939
I tasted a cream like this.

1284
00:45:43,373 --> 00:45:45,175
-In a good way or a bad way?
-Exactly.

1285
00:45:45,776 --> 00:45:47,878
-Does it feel odd? Unfamiliar?
-It's an emergency.

1286
00:45:48,445 --> 00:45:49,379
It's a first.

1287
00:45:49,446 --> 00:45:51,749
-She glared at you.
-Try it with the pollack roe.

1288
00:45:51,815 --> 00:45:53,350
-The pollack roe.
-All the way in.

1289
00:45:53,417 --> 00:45:54,852
IS IT AN EMERGENCY?

1290
00:45:54,918 --> 00:45:56,120
Okay. Not yet.

1291
00:45:56,186 --> 00:45:58,222
-She has never had it before.
-She could be unsure.

1292
00:45:59,089 --> 00:46:01,258
There's lots of stuff inside.

1293
00:46:01,325 --> 00:46:02,559
He used cheese too.

1294
00:46:02,626 --> 00:46:03,861
Yes, cheese and pollack roe.

1295
00:46:03,927 --> 00:46:04,762
GASPS

1296
00:46:05,529 --> 00:46:06,430
YAY

1297
00:46:06,497 --> 00:46:08,632
-Was it different? It must be good.
-It must be good.

1298
00:46:10,667 --> 00:46:11,702
SMILING

1299
00:46:11,769 --> 00:46:14,171
Is it different
from eating just the mousse?

1300
00:46:14,238 --> 00:46:15,472
-It's completely different.
-Completely.

1301
00:46:15,539 --> 00:46:16,840
-It could be hard at first.
-Yes.

1302
00:46:16,907 --> 00:46:18,642
-It's about the balance.
-Yes, the balance.

1303
00:46:18,709 --> 00:46:21,345
When I had just the mousse,

1304
00:46:21,411 --> 00:46:22,913
it felt like an ice cream salad.

1305
00:46:24,314 --> 00:46:27,618
I was a bit worried
that the pollack roe would be too salty

1306
00:46:27,684 --> 00:46:29,353
because the piece was a little big.

1307
00:46:29,419 --> 00:46:30,454
The cheese.

1308
00:46:30,521 --> 00:46:33,357
Yes, when it meets with the cheese,

1309
00:46:33,423 --> 00:46:35,359
the flavor turned very subtle.

1310
00:46:35,425 --> 00:46:36,760
They must go well together.

1311
00:46:36,827 --> 00:46:39,096
-It's so delicious.
-Thank you.

1312
00:46:39,163 --> 00:46:40,931
She says it's so delicious.

1313
00:46:41,598 --> 00:46:44,334
HEHE, NAM-NO IS HAPPY

1314
00:46:44,401 --> 00:46:46,870
The appetizer was a success.

1315
00:46:46,937 --> 00:46:49,573
She even licked the bits off her fingers.

1316
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:52,342
-The main dish.
-Next, <i>tteokgalbi</i> with abalone.

1317
00:46:52,409 --> 00:46:55,078
He put lots of work into that.

1318
00:46:55,145 --> 00:46:57,414
<i>He even used two big sticks of butter.</i>

1319
00:46:57,481 --> 00:47:00,117
It must be so nutritious.

1320
00:47:00,184 --> 00:47:02,820
It has everything but carbohydrates.

1321
00:47:02,886 --> 00:47:04,254
I wish I could try that too.

1322
00:47:04,321 --> 00:47:05,155
EYES GLUED

1323
00:47:05,756 --> 00:47:07,090
With the perilla leaves.

1324
00:47:07,157 --> 00:47:08,125
On top.

1325
00:47:08,192 --> 00:47:09,126
FIRST, A SMELL

1326
00:47:09,193 --> 00:47:10,460
She's about to try it.

1327
00:47:10,527 --> 00:47:11,628
What is it?

1328
00:47:11,695 --> 00:47:14,064
-It must smell good.
-She nodded at Nam-no.

1329
00:47:14,131 --> 00:47:15,666
My heart skipped a beat just now.

1330
00:47:15,732 --> 00:47:16,900
JUST ONE LOOK FROM NANA

1331
00:47:16,967 --> 00:47:19,837
He added some smoky flavor at the end.

1332
00:47:19,903 --> 00:47:21,271
Nam-no's heart skipped a beat.

1333
00:47:22,573 --> 00:47:25,676
She just tried <i>tteokgalbi </i>with abalone
with some perilla leaves.

1334
00:47:25,742 --> 00:47:28,312
I guess it doesn't hit you right away.

1335
00:47:29,079 --> 00:47:30,848
-She chews it for a while.
-Is it undercooked?

1336
00:47:30,914 --> 00:47:32,683
-Is she not moved?
-Mmm?

1337
00:47:32,749 --> 00:47:35,485
Let's pretend like he didn't make this
and only do the first one.

1338
00:47:35,552 --> 00:47:37,321
-As if he only made one dish?
-Yes.

1339
00:47:37,387 --> 00:47:39,523
-Should he end it with the avocado dish?
-Wait.

1340
00:47:40,357 --> 00:47:42,092
It tastes really healthy.

1341
00:47:42,159 --> 00:47:44,895
OH… IT TASTES HEALTHY?

1342
00:47:44,962 --> 00:47:47,598
I thought this would've held in
almost too much butter,

1343
00:47:47,664 --> 00:47:51,401
but it only added a subtle fragrance.

1344
00:47:51,468 --> 00:47:52,769
I immersed it in butter.

1345
00:47:52,836 --> 00:47:55,539
-Did you taste it?
-I couldn't.

1346
00:47:55,606 --> 00:47:58,242
-Is it seasoned well?
-The seasoning?

1347
00:47:58,308 --> 00:48:00,110
-Yes, it's not salty.
-It must taste light.

1348
00:48:00,177 --> 00:48:02,112
Yes, it mostly tastes light.

1349
00:48:02,179 --> 00:48:03,881
HMMM…

1350
00:48:03,947 --> 00:48:06,550
But it's not as greasy as you'd expect.

1351
00:48:06,617 --> 00:48:09,186
-I see. Right?
-I thought it would be too greasy.

1352
00:48:09,253 --> 00:48:11,488
It's like a patty
for a very high-quality hamburger.

1353
00:48:11,555 --> 00:48:13,790
A high-quality hamburger patty?

1354
00:48:13,857 --> 00:48:16,793
<i>Also, the abalone inside</i>

1355
00:48:16,860 --> 00:48:19,196
has been cooked perfectly tender.

1356
00:48:19,263 --> 00:48:20,964
-Was it cooked well?
-I'm glad.

1357
00:48:21,031 --> 00:48:24,201
When I feel down
and need a hearty amount of meat,

1358
00:48:24,268 --> 00:48:26,169
I'll probably crave this.

1359
00:48:27,070 --> 00:48:30,140
Why don't you top the mousse on the meat?

1360
00:48:30,207 --> 00:48:31,341
That's an idea.

1361
00:48:31,408 --> 00:48:33,343
-That's the intended way, right?
-It is.

1362
00:48:33,410 --> 00:48:35,679
-Is it?
-You're supposed to eat it together.

1363
00:48:35,746 --> 00:48:37,848
If that tastes weird,
it means you're done for good.

1364
00:48:37,915 --> 00:48:39,683
-It should be fine.
-It has to be good.

1365
00:48:39,750 --> 00:48:41,184
-It's like tacos.
-Yes.

1366
00:48:41,251 --> 00:48:42,886
A PIECE OF MEAT, A BITE OF MOUSSE

1367
00:48:42,953 --> 00:48:44,554
I wonder what the balance is like.

1368
00:48:44,621 --> 00:48:46,189
-Mmm.
-Mmm?

1369
00:48:47,057 --> 00:48:49,459
I think she just likes avocados.

1370
00:48:49,526 --> 00:48:50,394
IS THAT RIGHT?

1371
00:48:50,460 --> 00:48:51,695
-And pollack roe?
-And the roe.

1372
00:48:51,762 --> 00:48:53,864
IT'S THE BEST

1373
00:48:53,931 --> 00:48:55,265
She just likes salted pollack roe.

1374
00:48:55,332 --> 00:48:56,233
She likes salty food.

1375
00:48:56,300 --> 00:48:59,937
I really love cheese
and other rich ingredients,

1376
00:49:00,003 --> 00:49:01,204
-so these are good.
-Nice strategy.

1377
00:49:01,271 --> 00:49:03,140
Is it good together?

1378
00:49:03,206 --> 00:49:05,108
I like this mix much better.

1379
00:49:05,175 --> 00:49:06,810
-She's pleased with the mix.
-Yes.

1380
00:49:06,877 --> 00:49:09,846
I had this revelation
as I watched her eat just now.

1381
00:49:09,913 --> 00:49:11,848
She's on a no-carb, high-fat diet,

1382
00:49:11,915 --> 00:49:14,151
-but not low-sodium.
-She wants something strong.

1383
00:49:14,217 --> 00:49:16,620
She likes things
that have a bit of saltiness to it.

1384
00:49:16,687 --> 00:49:19,356
-Something strong and rich.
-I like my food salty. Yes.

1385
00:49:19,423 --> 00:49:22,359
You have a chance, Eun-yeong.

1386
00:49:22,426 --> 00:49:25,462
-Next, please try Chef Eun-yeong's dish.
-Look at that guy.

1387
00:49:25,529 --> 00:49:28,065
TIME TO TRY AMY PARK'S DISH!

1388
00:49:28,532 --> 00:49:31,902
"WESTERN FOOD ALWAYS COMES WITH A SALAD"
- AMY PARK -

1389
00:49:32,903 --> 00:49:37,140
SHANGHAI-STYLE LASAGNA
USING TOFU AS A PASTA SUBSTITUTE

1390
00:49:38,041 --> 00:49:41,878
CHEF AMY PARK'S SHANGHAI LASAGNA

1391
00:49:41,945 --> 00:49:44,114
-It looks salty.
-This must be so salty.

1392
00:49:44,181 --> 00:49:45,983
He'd be devastated
if he lost to her Western dish.

1393
00:49:46,049 --> 00:49:49,519
There's a lot of talk around this.
Is this Western food or Chinese food?

1394
00:49:49,586 --> 00:49:51,555
-And also…
-It obviously looks Italian.

1395
00:49:51,621 --> 00:49:54,891
…Chef Eun-yeong said,
"Western cuisine always serves a salad."

1396
00:49:54,958 --> 00:49:56,026
Should I begin with the salad?

1397
00:49:56,093 --> 00:49:58,929
Yes, have the salad first, just as
you always do with Western cuisine.

1398
00:49:58,996 --> 00:50:00,297
CONFIDENT AT ALL TIMES

1399
00:50:00,364 --> 00:50:02,065
-What's with her?
-She said that to me.

1400
00:50:02,132 --> 00:50:03,867
She said, "In Italy,

1401
00:50:03,934 --> 00:50:06,069
people eat salad to work up the appetite."

1402
00:50:06,136 --> 00:50:07,904
-In the order of Western cuisine.
-Yes, in the order.

1403
00:50:07,971 --> 00:50:10,807
Remember that she crushed
raw garlic cloves and threw it in there.

1404
00:50:10,874 --> 00:50:11,742
It's Western cuisine.

1405
00:50:12,542 --> 00:50:15,245
Does it taste like Western cuisine
or Chinese?

1406
00:50:15,812 --> 00:50:17,614
What's the salad like?

1407
00:50:18,482 --> 00:50:20,183
This smell…

1408
00:50:20,250 --> 00:50:21,685
SURPRISED!

1409
00:50:22,252 --> 00:50:24,221
I think it is the mix of the two.

1410
00:50:24,287 --> 00:50:25,389
Oh.

1411
00:50:25,922 --> 00:50:27,324
What do you mean, "Oh"?

1412
00:50:27,391 --> 00:50:29,393
-What's the mix?
-Chinese and Western.

1413
00:50:29,459 --> 00:50:30,460
-Chinese and Western.
-Chinese and Western.

1414
00:50:30,527 --> 00:50:32,763
-Is it a mix of Chinese and Western?
-Yes, it's a mix of the two.

1415
00:50:32,829 --> 00:50:33,897
I told you so.

1416
00:50:33,964 --> 00:50:36,500
I'm not sure what this smell is.

1417
00:50:36,566 --> 00:50:39,669
The raw garlic I added
brings out the Shanghai vibes,

1418
00:50:39,736 --> 00:50:42,606
but I also used
Oriental dressing and lemon juice,

1419
00:50:42,672 --> 00:50:44,808
and they add a touch of Italian.

1420
00:50:44,875 --> 00:50:47,144
What? How is Oriental dressing Italian?

1421
00:50:47,210 --> 00:50:51,181
-Don't you know what Oriental means?
-It's a soy-based dressing.

1422
00:50:51,248 --> 00:50:53,617
-Next, the main dish.
-<i>Mapo </i>tofu.

1423
00:50:53,683 --> 00:50:55,685
-Using a spoon.
-Eat it like you would lasagna.

1424
00:50:55,752 --> 00:50:58,021
Dig down all the way to the bottom
and scoop up a bite.

1425
00:50:58,088 --> 00:50:59,723
-It looks good.
-Get every layer.

1426
00:51:00,290 --> 00:51:02,025
<i>She substituted pasta with tofu</i>

1427
00:51:02,092 --> 00:51:04,361
<i>to get rid of carbs.</i>

1428
00:51:04,761 --> 00:51:06,663
WILL IT DO ITS PART AS PASTA?

1429
00:51:06,730 --> 00:51:08,598
Will the tofu act like pasta?

1430
00:51:08,665 --> 00:51:13,370
To me, that sauce was a bit salty.
I wonder if it'll be okay.

1431
00:51:13,437 --> 00:51:15,472
She seemed to like her food salty.

1432
00:51:16,339 --> 00:51:18,208
-Her diet isn't low-sodium.
-No.

1433
00:51:18,275 --> 00:51:20,444
This is the main dish. Shanghai Lasagna.

1434
00:51:20,510 --> 00:51:21,511
A BIG BITE

1435
00:51:22,679 --> 00:51:23,513
GASP!

1436
00:51:24,681 --> 00:51:26,550
SHE'S SURPRISED TOO

1437
00:51:26,616 --> 00:51:28,251
-Why are you surprised?
-Emergency, Nam-no.

1438
00:51:28,318 --> 00:51:29,553
An emergency for Nam-no?

1439
00:51:30,120 --> 00:51:31,621
-Is it seasoned well?
-It must be perfect.

1440
00:51:32,722 --> 00:51:34,024
VERY MUCH

1441
00:51:34,091 --> 00:51:36,460
What she wanted was
no-carb, high-fat, and high-sodium!

1442
00:51:36,526 --> 00:51:38,528
WHO EATS HER FOOD SALTY? NANA!

1443
00:51:38,595 --> 00:51:40,764
Pretty girls like their food salty.

1444
00:51:40,831 --> 00:51:43,400
It could've been saltier
because of this cheddar,

1445
00:51:43,467 --> 00:51:46,002
but it doesn't taste overly salty.

1446
00:51:47,370 --> 00:51:50,040
Also, food is seasoned strongly in Italy,

1447
00:51:50,107 --> 00:51:54,311
so I made it a little saltier.
It must've suited that Italian dish.

1448
00:51:54,377 --> 00:51:56,213
She's practically Italian now.

1449
00:51:56,279 --> 00:51:57,948
-Why didn't you season the tofu?
-What?

1450
00:51:58,014 --> 00:52:00,417
The sauce is salty,
so the tofu didn't need any salt.

1451
00:52:00,484 --> 00:52:02,119
You don't season noodles
in Chinese cuisine.

1452
00:52:02,185 --> 00:52:05,288
She thought it'd be saltier
because of the cheddar,

1453
00:52:05,355 --> 00:52:06,590
but it isn't salty.

1454
00:52:06,656 --> 00:52:08,291
Do you think it's a Western dish?

1455
00:52:08,358 --> 00:52:09,626
Yes, completely.

1456
00:52:09,693 --> 00:52:13,530
-I mean, it tastes really good!
-Doesn't it?

1457
00:52:13,597 --> 00:52:16,333
-If it's good, it's Western.
-Yes, sure.

1458
00:52:16,399 --> 00:52:18,235
It's also a bit spicy.

1459
00:52:18,301 --> 00:52:20,170
I added some Buldak sauce.

1460
00:52:20,237 --> 00:52:23,173
Also, it must taste like a Western dish

1461
00:52:23,240 --> 00:52:26,042
because I added a spoon of ice cream.

1462
00:52:26,109 --> 00:52:28,745
-Ice cream equals Western food?
-Ice cream?

1463
00:52:28,812 --> 00:52:30,280
It added flavorful sweetness.

1464
00:52:30,347 --> 00:52:33,216
Can you tell us what it's like?

1465
00:52:33,283 --> 00:52:34,751
It tastes like lasagna.

1466
00:52:34,818 --> 00:52:35,952
-It tastes like lasagna?
-It tastes like lasagna?

1467
00:52:36,019 --> 00:52:37,287
It tastes like spicy lasagna.

1468
00:52:37,354 --> 00:52:39,222
-Spicy lasagna.
-Spicy lasagna.

1469
00:52:39,289 --> 00:52:43,160
The only difference is the texture
because she used tofu.

1470
00:52:43,226 --> 00:52:45,629
-But it's a familiar taste.
-It's an emergency, Nam-no.

1471
00:52:45,695 --> 00:52:48,498
-Should I open a pasta joint?
-She approves it as a Western dish.

1472
00:52:48,565 --> 00:52:51,668
Why don't you try it too, Kyuhyun?

1473
00:52:51,735 --> 00:52:53,570
He tries the mousse.

1474
00:52:53,637 --> 00:52:54,704
What's it like?

1475
00:52:56,740 --> 00:52:58,708
-Gosh.
-What's up?

1476
00:52:58,775 --> 00:53:02,612
The salted pollack roe is pretty salty.

1477
00:53:02,679 --> 00:53:05,315
I had a huge piece,
but it wasn't salty at all.

1478
00:53:05,382 --> 00:53:07,284
-She likes her food salty.
-She does.

1479
00:53:07,350 --> 00:53:09,786
-She likes her food salty.
-Whose tune do I have to dance to?

1480
00:53:09,853 --> 00:53:11,721
It's no-carb, high-fat, and high-sodium.

1481
00:53:11,788 --> 00:53:13,390
-This is a high-sodium dish.
-It is?

1482
00:53:13,456 --> 00:53:16,626
Anyway, when it mixes with the apple,

1483
00:53:16,693 --> 00:53:19,329
the saltiness gets covered by the cream,

1484
00:53:19,396 --> 00:53:20,931
so overall, the balance is great.

1485
00:53:21,364 --> 00:53:22,432
THAT'S IT

1486
00:53:22,499 --> 00:53:23,900
The overall balance is good.

1487
00:53:24,401 --> 00:53:26,102
NEXT, TTEOKGALBI WITH ABALONE

1488
00:53:26,169 --> 00:53:27,137
<i>Tteokgalbi </i>with abalone.

1489
00:53:27,204 --> 00:53:29,339
-I love the smokiness.
-He loves the smokiness.

1490
00:53:29,406 --> 00:53:33,243
He was surprised when he saw Nam-no
put the abalone on the meat.

1491
00:53:34,477 --> 00:53:36,379
How do you like it, Kyuhyun?

1492
00:53:36,446 --> 00:53:38,215
Does it taste light or too salty?

1493
00:53:39,482 --> 00:53:40,951
NERVOUS

1494
00:53:41,017 --> 00:53:42,519
-It tastes healthy.
-It tastes healthy.

1495
00:53:42,586 --> 00:53:43,787
-Healthy.
-It's light.

1496
00:53:43,853 --> 00:53:47,023
But I can sense that the chef has put in

1497
00:53:47,090 --> 00:53:50,727
a lot of thought into the dish
to serve it to a guest.

1498
00:53:50,794 --> 00:53:53,096
-Does it feel considerate?
-It does.

1499
00:53:53,163 --> 00:53:56,366
Next, Chef Eun-yeong's Shanghai Lasagna.

1500
00:53:56,433 --> 00:53:57,634
IN PROPER ORDER
SALAD FIRST

1501
00:53:57,701 --> 00:54:00,136
Does it taste Western or Chinese?

1502
00:54:00,203 --> 00:54:01,938
TRYING NOT TO LAUGH

1503
00:54:02,005 --> 00:54:03,039
Well,

1504
00:54:03,773 --> 00:54:06,142
-this is Western cuisine.
-It is?

1505
00:54:06,209 --> 00:54:09,379
She used raw garlic,
but it's still Western cuisine.

1506
00:54:09,446 --> 00:54:11,181
The raw garlic doesn't get in the way.

1507
00:54:11,248 --> 00:54:15,852
Rather, it helps refresh your palate
with a bit of bitter spiciness.

1508
00:54:15,919 --> 00:54:17,854
Eun-yeong has made Western dishes today.

1509
00:54:17,921 --> 00:54:21,124
Next, Shanghai Lasagna,
made with tofu instead of lasagna noodles.

1510
00:54:23,493 --> 00:54:25,762
SON'S HAND WITH GOOD MANNERS

1511
00:54:26,463 --> 00:54:28,298
I wonder what it's like.

1512
00:54:28,365 --> 00:54:29,833
HE CHUCKLES?

1513
00:54:29,899 --> 00:54:31,868
GLARING

1514
00:54:31,935 --> 00:54:33,737
What is it? Why are you looking at her?

1515
00:54:33,803 --> 00:54:35,005
WHAT IS IT?

1516
00:54:35,071 --> 00:54:37,173
-Is there a problem?
-Look at her face.

1517
00:54:38,308 --> 00:54:39,643
It's so good.

1518
00:54:41,378 --> 00:54:42,212
Eun-yeong!

1519
00:54:42,279 --> 00:54:44,180
-Gosh.
-Eun-yeong!

1520
00:54:44,247 --> 00:54:45,682
This is a huge twist!

1521
00:54:45,749 --> 00:54:49,052
-I'm getting a headache.
-Is it Chinese or Western?

1522
00:54:49,119 --> 00:54:50,954
-Amy did this?
-Is it really good?

1523
00:54:51,021 --> 00:54:52,889
-It's lasagna…
-Amy Park?

1524
00:54:52,956 --> 00:54:53,857
…but a spicy version.

1525
00:54:53,923 --> 00:54:55,158
TOTALLY!

1526
00:54:55,225 --> 00:54:57,394
Also, I keep craving more.

1527
00:54:57,460 --> 00:54:59,195
TAKES A BITE OUT OF CURIOSITY

1528
00:54:59,262 --> 00:55:00,797
Kyuhyun is rather surprised.

1529
00:55:00,864 --> 00:55:02,565
ANOTHER GLARE

1530
00:55:02,632 --> 00:55:04,567
-Try it. Does it taste Western?
-I had it.

1531
00:55:04,634 --> 00:55:08,805
There's this particular chef,
no, maybe a webtoon artist, on this show.

1532
00:55:08,872 --> 00:55:11,641
There's a twist
to the dishes that he makes, right?

1533
00:55:11,708 --> 00:55:13,576
-I had the same feeling.
-The same feeling?

1534
00:55:13,643 --> 00:55:16,546
-I keep seeing Poong in her.
-In Chef Eun-yeong?

1535
00:55:16,613 --> 00:55:18,081
She used the Poong strategy.

1536
00:55:18,148 --> 00:55:20,684
I wonder who that person is.

1537
00:55:20,750 --> 00:55:23,219
-He said he was a webtoon artist.
-A webtoon artist?

1538
00:55:23,286 --> 00:55:25,755
The fridge owner will make the decision.

1539
00:55:25,822 --> 00:55:29,359
Nana, please decide the winner.

1540
00:55:29,426 --> 00:55:32,228
<i>Press one for Chef Eun-yeong</i>

1541
00:55:32,295 --> 00:55:33,897
<i>and two for Nam-no.</i>

1542
00:55:34,931 --> 00:55:37,901
Whose dish did she enjoy more?

1543
00:55:37,967 --> 00:55:40,470
Let's find out the result. Show us!

1544
00:55:41,705 --> 00:55:44,908
Will Nam-no win his first star?

1545
00:55:44,974 --> 00:55:48,078
Or will Eun-yeong whip him once again?

1546
00:55:48,745 --> 00:55:51,681
Who won this round?

1547
00:55:52,716 --> 00:55:54,250
Who is it?

1548
00:55:54,317 --> 00:55:55,752
SURPRISED

1549
00:55:56,653 --> 00:55:58,254
YOON NAM-NO WINS

1550
00:55:58,321 --> 00:55:59,422
Yoon Nam-no wins!

1551
00:55:59,489 --> 00:56:02,258
CHEF YOON NAM-NO'S YOON NAM-NO CARBS WINS

1552
00:56:02,325 --> 00:56:03,860
Yoon Nam-no wins!

1553
00:56:05,095 --> 00:56:08,398
-Nana chose Nam-no!
-Great job.

1554
00:56:09,032 --> 00:56:12,569
THE RESULT WAS ONE TWIST AFTER ANOTHER

1555
00:56:12,635 --> 00:56:15,872
Both dishes were delicious,
so it was hard to decide.

1556
00:56:15,939 --> 00:56:19,376
You two both made two dishes for me,

1557
00:56:19,442 --> 00:56:23,913
<i>so I thought about which two dishes had</i>
<i>a better balance if eaten together.</i>

1558
00:56:23,980 --> 00:56:28,651
That was why I gave
a higher score to his dishes.

1559
00:56:28,718 --> 00:56:29,719
The salad.

1560
00:56:29,786 --> 00:56:32,455
Chef Nam-no's main dish
had a better balance

1561
00:56:32,522 --> 00:56:34,591
with the salad he served.

1562
00:56:34,657 --> 00:56:36,092
But both were delicious.

1563
00:56:36,159 --> 00:56:38,728
-He worked hard on the avocado.
-He did.

1564
00:56:38,795 --> 00:56:40,497
This means since the new year,

1565
00:56:40,563 --> 00:56:43,233
-it took him until the end of March…
-What a relief.

1566
00:56:43,299 --> 00:56:45,602
…to take his first star.

1567
00:56:45,668 --> 00:56:47,837
It was my first time
losing three rounds in a row

1568
00:56:47,904 --> 00:56:48,838
until very recently.

1569
00:56:48,905 --> 00:56:50,974
I felt so burdened
that I was scared of the shoot.

1570
00:56:51,040 --> 00:56:53,042
-Yes, it's a burden.
-I'm glad that ended today.

1571
00:56:53,109 --> 00:56:55,044
In the future,
I won't lose three times in a row,

1572
00:56:55,111 --> 00:56:56,713
but will try to win three times in a row.

1573
00:56:56,780 --> 00:56:58,982
-Thank you.
-Congratulations.

1574
00:56:59,549 --> 00:57:01,418
Nam-no finally takes

1575
00:57:01,484 --> 00:57:04,487
-his long-awaited first win! Congrats!
-Thank you.

1576
00:57:04,554 --> 00:57:07,123
-Congratulations!
-He wins his first star!

1577
00:57:07,190 --> 00:57:09,092
Nam-no's journey begins now.

1578
00:57:10,360 --> 00:57:14,030
<i>This is the second cook-off played</i>
<i>with ingredients from Nana's fridge.</i>

1579
00:57:14,097 --> 00:57:16,166
Who Wants to Delete Mom's Ingredients?

1580
00:57:16,232 --> 00:57:17,200
-Me, Me!
-Me, Me!

1581
00:57:17,267 --> 00:57:18,334
Me, Me!

1582
00:57:18,401 --> 00:57:21,838
This round is between
Chef Sam Kim, the canine villain,

1583
00:57:21,905 --> 00:57:24,541
-and the clout villain, Chef Sung-jun.
-His canine is so scary.

1584
00:57:24,607 --> 00:57:26,709
Now that Kang-rok has returned,

1585
00:57:26,776 --> 00:57:31,781
many must have expected to see
a round between him and Sung-jun.

1586
00:57:31,848 --> 00:57:34,150
Well, I have many strategies.

1587
00:57:34,217 --> 00:57:35,785
First of all,

1588
00:57:35,852 --> 00:57:37,353
if viewers want to see that,

1589
00:57:37,420 --> 00:57:38,555
we should delay it

1590
00:57:38,621 --> 00:57:40,990
as much as we can
to maintain our popularity longer.

1591
00:57:41,057 --> 00:57:42,158
A STEP BACK FOR ATTENTION

1592
00:57:42,225 --> 00:57:45,728
-Really?
-Also, recently, Chef Sam

1593
00:57:45,795 --> 00:57:47,997
has been going very strong.

1594
00:57:48,064 --> 00:57:51,601
-He's right.
-Not only has he won many stars,

1595
00:57:51,668 --> 00:57:53,803
but I have kept an eye on him and noticed

1596
00:57:53,870 --> 00:57:56,506
that he had the highest rate of rise
in the number of followers.

1597
00:57:56,573 --> 00:57:59,309
-He now has the third most followers here.
-I see.

1598
00:57:59,375 --> 00:58:02,045
-He had been well under Chef Hyun-suk.
-Under?

1599
00:58:02,111 --> 00:58:04,614
-"Under."
-He surpassed him.

1600
00:58:04,681 --> 00:58:07,717
He once went around
with a book of Hyun-suk's quotes.

1601
00:58:07,784 --> 00:58:09,319
-Yes.
-Do you remember?

1602
00:58:09,385 --> 00:58:11,321
But recently, he won't even talk to him.

1603
00:58:12,021 --> 00:58:13,590
CHOI HYUN-SUK? QUOTES?

1604
00:58:13,656 --> 00:58:14,824
He doesn't even say hi.

1605
00:58:14,891 --> 00:58:15,925
-This is…
-He doesn't.

1606
00:58:15,992 --> 00:58:17,560
In the world of culinary arts,

1607
00:58:17,627 --> 00:58:18,962
I have been buried alive.

1608
00:58:19,362 --> 00:58:21,030
LOVES THIS KIND OF JOKE

1609
00:58:21,097 --> 00:58:22,932
-His knee surgery is already sad enough.
-It is.

1610
00:58:22,999 --> 00:58:24,334
He's now less buzzworthy.

1611
00:58:24,400 --> 00:58:26,970
It's so heartbreaking.

1612
00:58:27,036 --> 00:58:28,872
It may seem like

1613
00:58:28,938 --> 00:58:32,342
Chef Sam
always talks so nicely like a saint.

1614
00:58:32,408 --> 00:58:34,244
But we have a transcript
from the greenroom.

1615
00:58:34,310 --> 00:58:36,346
-We were deeply shocked.
-Really?

1616
00:58:36,412 --> 00:58:39,349
-"Sung-jun's weakness is…
-He talked about his weakness?

1617
00:58:39,415 --> 00:58:41,251
…that he looks older than his age."

1618
00:58:41,751 --> 00:58:43,019
OH, NO

1619
00:58:43,086 --> 00:58:45,221
This is closer to an insult.

1620
00:58:45,288 --> 00:58:47,490
-A mistake.
-His weakness isn't in cooking.

1621
00:58:47,557 --> 00:58:50,159
-His old face, a mistake.
-He judged him by his looks.

1622
00:58:50,226 --> 00:58:52,395
It's not my opinion.
I was reiterating someone's words.

1623
00:58:52,462 --> 00:58:53,530
PFFT

1624
00:58:53,596 --> 00:58:56,499
People who pass things along
are worse than those who say it.

1625
00:58:57,166 --> 00:58:59,636
-Those who pass things on are worse!
-You're right!

1626
00:58:59,702 --> 00:59:01,738
-I don't think it impacts him in any way.
-Why not?

1627
00:59:01,804 --> 00:59:04,274
It's something that we all already know.

1628
00:59:04,340 --> 00:59:05,341
EVERYONE ALREADY KNOWS

1629
00:59:05,408 --> 00:59:06,776
We have a group chat without you.

1630
00:59:06,843 --> 00:59:08,511
-I knew that.
-We said it there.

1631
00:59:08,578 --> 00:59:10,013
You aren't supposed to tell him.

1632
00:59:10,079 --> 00:59:11,814
To be honest, I wanted to look that way.

1633
00:59:11,881 --> 00:59:13,349
Was it intentional?

1634
00:59:13,416 --> 00:59:16,185
It's better for a chef
to be more experienced with age.

1635
00:59:16,252 --> 00:59:17,820
It earns you more respect.

1636
00:59:17,887 --> 00:59:20,089
It's a closed-off group of people.

1637
00:59:20,156 --> 00:59:21,724
JEEZ

1638
00:59:21,791 --> 00:59:23,426
-A closed-off group?
-Closed-off?

1639
00:59:23,493 --> 00:59:25,528
That was why I wanted to look older.

1640
00:59:25,595 --> 00:59:26,896
-Chef Kang-rok.
-Yes?

1641
00:59:26,963 --> 00:59:30,700
Is it an advantage in the culinary world
to look older than your age?

1642
00:59:30,767 --> 00:59:32,969
-It's nice to be young.
-Yes, it's nice to be young.

1643
00:59:33,036 --> 00:59:34,537
It's nice to be young.

1644
00:59:34,604 --> 00:59:37,340
Actually, I thought he looked younger

1645
00:59:37,407 --> 00:59:39,075
because he reminds me
of my middle school self.

1646
00:59:39,142 --> 00:59:41,277
I had that hair
before the student hair code was lifted.

1647
00:59:41,344 --> 00:59:42,946
YOU'RE RIGHT

1648
00:59:43,012 --> 00:59:45,548
LOOKS LIKE A MIDDLE SCHOOL STUDENT

1649
00:59:45,615 --> 00:59:47,150
-With hair gel.
-That was my hair.

1650
00:59:47,216 --> 00:59:49,319
KYUHYUN APPROVES SUNG-JUN AS A YOUNGSTER

1651
00:59:50,153 --> 00:59:52,822
CHEF SUNG-JUN'S INGREDIENTS: RADISH,
BRAISED SHORT RIBS, BRAISED RIBS

1652
00:59:52,889 --> 00:59:55,525
MASCARPONE, CHEDDAR, CUBED CHEESE,
STRING CHEESE, PEAR, APPLE, AND MORE

1653
00:59:55,592 --> 00:59:57,961
What are you making, Chef Sung-jun?

1654
00:59:58,027 --> 00:59:59,095
It's Magic Pizza.

1655
00:59:59,162 --> 01:00:00,129
-Magic Pizza?
-Magic Pizza.

1656
01:00:00,196 --> 01:00:02,365
-Magic Pizza.
-Magic Pizza

1657
01:00:02,432 --> 01:00:05,668
Nana said she uses radishes instead
of potatoes to make braised chicken,

1658
01:00:05,735 --> 01:00:08,004
and that was where I got my idea.

1659
01:00:08,071 --> 01:00:09,973
She also said she likes Chicago pizza,

1660
01:00:10,039 --> 01:00:11,975
so I'll use radish
and make radish-cago pizza.

1661
01:00:12,041 --> 01:00:13,776
-What?
-Radish-cago?

1662
01:00:13,843 --> 01:00:15,578
I'll use radish as the dough.

1663
01:00:15,645 --> 01:00:16,980
-I see.
-Radish?

1664
01:00:17,046 --> 01:00:19,716
Then I'll use braised ribs as the topping.

1665
01:00:19,782 --> 01:00:21,718
Lastly, four-cheese.

1666
01:00:21,784 --> 01:00:23,553
I'll throw in lots of cheese

1667
01:00:23,620 --> 01:00:25,221
and bake it in the oven.

1668
01:00:25,288 --> 01:00:29,292
Fruits go bad the quickest,
so I'll use lots of those

1669
01:00:29,359 --> 01:00:30,426
and make Italian fruit salad,

1670
01:00:30,493 --> 01:00:33,262
something called Macedonia.

1671
01:00:33,329 --> 01:00:35,365
You'll make Macedonia?

1672
01:00:36,199 --> 01:00:38,601
CHEF SAM'S INGREDIENTS: STRIP LOIN,
SCALLOP, SQUID, ABALONE, VENUS CLAM

1673
01:00:38,668 --> 01:00:40,370
ORANGE, MANGO, SALAD MIX,
BOK CHOY, LEMON, AND MORE

1674
01:00:40,436 --> 01:00:43,439
Up against him is Sam Kim.
What are you making?

1675
01:00:43,506 --> 01:00:45,408
Here's the name of my dish.

1676
01:00:45,475 --> 01:00:46,576
DETERMINED

1677
01:00:46,643 --> 01:00:47,744
Magic Pizza?

1678
01:00:47,810 --> 01:00:49,178
-Hah!
-Hah!

1679
01:00:50,313 --> 01:00:51,314
Hah!

1680
01:00:52,215 --> 01:00:53,182
Hah!

1681
01:00:54,150 --> 01:00:55,985
HEADS DROP DOWN

1682
01:00:56,052 --> 01:00:58,955
-Just like that? Hah!
-Magic Pizza? Hah!

1683
01:00:59,022 --> 01:01:01,958
SAM, EVEN YOU…

1684
01:01:02,025 --> 01:01:03,693
Magic Pizza? Hah!

1685
01:01:03,760 --> 01:01:05,328
You got nothing on me. Hah!

1686
01:01:05,395 --> 01:01:08,031
TAKING THE LEAD WITH THE DISH NAME

1687
01:01:08,097 --> 01:01:09,799
I also prepared two different dishes.

1688
01:01:09,866 --> 01:01:13,002
First, I'll use some seafood
and make a seafood salad.

1689
01:01:13,569 --> 01:01:15,905
I'll deep-fry onion, stuff it with meat,

1690
01:01:15,972 --> 01:01:17,040
and roast it a little.

1691
01:01:17,774 --> 01:01:20,143
I'll also make use of the ingredients

1692
01:01:20,209 --> 01:01:21,778
your mother so lovingly got for you.

1693
01:01:23,312 --> 01:01:25,448
All right.
Let's begin the 15-minute cook-off.

1694
01:01:26,015 --> 01:01:29,619
Who Wants to Delete Mom's Ingredients?
Who will it be?

1695
01:01:29,686 --> 01:01:33,423
This man wants to delete
all of Sam Kim's followers.

1696
01:01:33,489 --> 01:01:35,958
The clout villain, Chef Kwon Sung-jun.

1697
01:01:36,025 --> 01:01:39,862
This man wants to delete the teeth
from Sung-jun's talkative mouth.

1698
01:01:39,929 --> 01:01:43,533
The canine villain, Chef Sam Kim.

1699
01:01:43,599 --> 01:01:44,534
ONE PUNCH!

1700
01:01:44,600 --> 01:01:46,269
AND THREE TEETH FALL OUT!

1701
01:01:46,335 --> 01:01:48,771
Who will Nana choose?

1702
01:01:48,838 --> 01:01:51,908
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1703
01:01:52,442 --> 01:01:53,443
You got this!

1704
01:01:53,509 --> 01:01:55,678
THE ITALIAN CUISINE DELETION MATCH!

1705
01:01:55,745 --> 01:01:57,246
BRAISED SHORT RIBS IN SOY SAUCE,
SPICY RIBS

1706
01:01:57,313 --> 01:01:58,881
What are you pouring into the pan?

1707
01:01:58,948 --> 01:02:00,616
-These? Ribs.
-Ribs.

1708
01:02:00,683 --> 01:02:02,452
-Yes.
-She had that?

1709
01:02:02,518 --> 01:02:03,986
If he wants to make Chicago pizza,

1710
01:02:04,053 --> 01:02:06,756
he'll need something deep enough
to hold everything in.

1711
01:02:06,823 --> 01:02:10,126
-So he'll have to dig out the radish.
-To hold the toppings in.

1712
01:02:10,193 --> 01:02:14,497
She prefers radishes in braised chicken
instead of potatoes.

1713
01:02:15,064 --> 01:02:16,733
He's digging it out, as I expected.

1714
01:02:16,799 --> 01:02:17,934
He's digging it out.

1715
01:02:18,000 --> 01:02:19,535
Yes, he's digging it out.

1716
01:02:19,602 --> 01:02:22,004
He'll probably fill that up.

1717
01:02:22,071 --> 01:02:24,474
-That radish?
-He'll use it as the dough.

1718
01:02:24,540 --> 01:02:27,143
That means his pizza will be quite small.

1719
01:02:27,210 --> 01:02:29,679
Well, it's only for Nana, anyway.

1720
01:02:29,746 --> 01:02:31,647
It doesn't need to be huge.

1721
01:02:31,714 --> 01:02:32,982
Only she needs to eat it.

1722
01:02:33,049 --> 01:02:34,984
-He pours hot water over it.
-Whoa.

1723
01:02:35,051 --> 01:02:37,920
It won't cook thoroughly in the oven,
so he's cooking it ahead of time.

1724
01:02:37,987 --> 01:02:38,955
Yes, with hot water.

1725
01:02:39,021 --> 01:02:41,724
What are you adding?
Are you braising the radish?

1726
01:02:41,791 --> 01:02:43,926
Yes, I'm trying to cook the radish.

1727
01:02:43,993 --> 01:02:46,229
-He's adding sauce to season it.
-He's using the microwave.

1728
01:02:46,295 --> 01:02:48,164
-…as he cooks it in the microwave.
-Yes.

1729
01:02:48,231 --> 01:02:50,933
It'll take a while
for something that thick to cook.

1730
01:02:51,000 --> 01:02:52,268
I think he poured hot water.

1731
01:02:52,335 --> 01:02:53,469
Yes, I used hot water.

1732
01:02:53,536 --> 01:02:55,938
-Is it hot water?
-It is.

1733
01:02:56,005 --> 01:02:59,142
It'll take at least five to seven minutes.

1734
01:02:59,776 --> 01:03:00,610
Hah!

1735
01:03:00,676 --> 01:03:03,713
-Onion.
-Is that an onion?

1736
01:03:03,780 --> 01:03:06,115
-Yes, it's an onion.
-An onion.

1737
01:03:06,182 --> 01:03:08,918
-Did you throw it in oil?
-Yes, it's oil.

1738
01:03:08,985 --> 01:03:11,187
DICING THE REMAINDER

1739
01:03:11,254 --> 01:03:12,121
OLIVE OIL

1740
01:03:12,188 --> 01:03:13,322
MINCED ONION, CRUSHED GARLIC

1741
01:03:13,389 --> 01:03:14,223
Bok choy.

1742
01:03:14,290 --> 01:03:16,159
Oyster sauce.

1743
01:03:16,225 --> 01:03:18,027
-Oyster sauce?
-He just poured it in.

1744
01:03:18,094 --> 01:03:20,563
Bok choy and oyster sauce?
It smells like Chinese food.

1745
01:03:20,630 --> 01:03:22,498
-It's Sam's Chinese Cuisine.
-Yes.

1746
01:03:22,565 --> 01:03:25,134
STRIP LOIN
CHINESE RESTAURANT, HUI-TAE'S DINER!

1747
01:03:25,201 --> 01:03:26,102
