1827
01:06:12,802 --> 01:06:15,304
-Fruit over shaved ice… No, fruit salad.
-It's a mango.

1828
01:06:15,371 --> 01:06:16,572
-Isn't that a mango?
-It's a mango.

1829
01:06:16,639 --> 01:06:18,207
-A mango.
-It's not an avocado. It's a mango.

1830
01:06:18,274 --> 01:06:19,342
It's a mango.

1831
01:06:19,408 --> 01:06:22,745
It's very difficult
to get mango and avocado mixed up.

1832
01:06:24,180 --> 01:06:27,650
HAHAHAHAHA…

1833
01:06:28,184 --> 01:06:31,220
I've never seen an avocado that big.
And in that color.

1834
01:06:31,287 --> 01:06:32,922
-Wait.
-It looks like radish kimchi.

1835
01:06:32,989 --> 01:06:35,391
-Why does it seem so hard?
-It's so hard.

1836
01:06:35,458 --> 01:06:37,226
-It's like Korean melon.
-It's not ripe, is it?

1837
01:06:37,293 --> 01:06:38,594
-It's not.
-It's not ripe yet.

1838
01:06:39,729 --> 01:06:41,564
-Whoa.
-Is it okay? Isn't it too hard?

1839
01:06:41,630 --> 01:06:43,666
Sam uses a mango too.

1840
01:06:43,733 --> 01:06:44,867
-It's…
-This one too?

1841
01:06:44,934 --> 01:06:46,369
Sam's mango is firmer.

1842
01:06:46,435 --> 01:06:47,703
I doubt I can use this.

1843
01:06:47,770 --> 01:06:48,804
Have a taste.

1844
01:06:48,871 --> 01:06:52,141
It's probably not bitter,
but a little more sour than usual.

1845
01:06:52,208 --> 01:06:53,309
YUM

1846
01:06:53,376 --> 01:06:54,477
What is this?

1847
01:06:55,077 --> 01:06:56,012
Is this a peach?

1848
01:06:56,078 --> 01:06:57,346
It really is sour.

1849
01:06:57,413 --> 01:06:58,981
The mangoes are good.
Use lots of them.

1850
01:06:59,048 --> 01:07:01,617
-Are they? I will.
-Yes.

1851
