1922
01:09:19,455 --> 01:09:21,490
-but nothing is ready.
-Wait, I don't have time.

1923
01:09:21,557 --> 01:09:22,958
You don't have much time.

1924
01:09:24,493 --> 01:09:25,895
Is it cooked?

1925
01:09:25,961 --> 01:09:27,530
So? Is it?

1926
01:09:28,063 --> 01:09:29,398
SOFT!

1927
01:09:29,465 --> 01:09:30,399
It's cooked.

1928
01:09:30,966 --> 01:09:32,301
It's cooked.

1929
01:09:32,368 --> 01:09:33,936
Drain and cook it for another minute.

1930
01:09:34,003 --> 01:09:36,739
After draining it? But it's cooked.

1931
01:09:37,473 --> 01:09:38,774
-It must be cooked well.
-It's cooked.

1932
01:09:38,841 --> 01:09:41,010
Hey, watch out.

1933
01:09:41,477 --> 01:09:42,945
SURPRISED

1934
01:09:43,012 --> 01:09:43,913
He can't get it out.

1935
01:09:44,914 --> 01:09:47,116
-The radish!
-He can't get it out.

1936
01:09:47,183 --> 01:09:49,385
The chef who can't feel heat
is feeling the heat now!

1937
01:09:49,451 --> 01:09:51,253
<i>I cannot feel heat.</i>

1938
01:09:51,320 --> 01:09:52,354
Feel the pain, young one.

1939
01:09:52,421 --> 01:09:53,822
-What?
-The radish.

1940
01:09:53,889 --> 01:09:56,926
-What?
-The radish. It's hot.

1941
01:09:56,992 --> 01:09:58,561
-He's a liar!
-Like this?

1942
01:09:58,627 --> 01:10:01,197
-It must've been too hot.
-It must've been.

1943
01:10:01,263 --> 01:10:02,431
NOT SHAKEN, DESPITE THE ATTACKS

1944
01:10:04,133 --> 01:10:05,568
Oh, no.

1945
01:10:05,634 --> 01:10:07,503
-I'm concerned.
-The cheese is a bit burnt!

1946
01:10:07,570 --> 01:10:09,305
No, it's the Maillard reaction.

1947
01:10:09,371 --> 01:10:10,639
-The Maillard reaction?
-Yes.

1948
01:10:10,706 --> 01:10:12,074
HIS PSYCHE IS NEVER SHAKEN

1949
01:10:12,141 --> 01:10:14,143
Jung-hwan, will you try the cheese?

1950
01:10:14,210 --> 01:10:15,411
The cheese?

1951
01:10:15,477 --> 01:10:17,880
-Sung-jun said it was good.
-He said it was insane.

1952
01:10:17,947 --> 01:10:20,216
-What's the cheese like?
-It's hot.

1953
01:10:20,282 --> 01:10:22,318
He tried it and said it was insane.

1954
01:10:22,384 --> 01:10:23,919
Is it magical?

1955
01:10:23,986 --> 01:10:25,421
Or was it a mistake?

1956
01:10:26,589 --> 01:10:28,424
What's the cheese like?

1957
01:10:29,058 --> 01:10:30,059
It's closer to magical!

1958
01:10:30,125 --> 01:10:31,427
Whoa. Is it good?

1959
01:10:31,493 --> 01:10:32,761
It is.

1960
01:10:33,529 --> 01:10:35,531
It's good when everything's mixed.

1961
01:10:35,598 --> 01:10:36,665
How many did you use?

1962
01:10:36,732 --> 01:10:39,001
-Four. It's <i>quattro</i> cheese.
-Four-cheese.

1963
01:10:39,068 --> 01:10:40,869
<i>Quattro</i>-cheese.

1964
01:10:40,936 --> 01:10:43,138
Then it'll taste amazing
with some meat on top.

1965
01:10:43,205 --> 01:10:44,340
He's dicing it.

1966
01:10:44,406 --> 01:10:45,507
The cheese is good.

1967
01:10:45,574 --> 01:10:47,009
He begins to fill the radish.

1968
01:10:47,076 --> 01:10:48,277
The radish is ready.

1969
01:10:49,078 --> 01:10:50,346
SAM BEGINS TO PLATE THE DISH

1970
01:10:51,547 --> 01:10:53,182
A MIX OF MINCED ONION AND MANGO

1971
01:10:53,782 --> 01:10:55,217
What's this sauce?

1972
01:10:55,284 --> 01:10:57,219
It's balsamic vinegar.

1973
01:10:57,286 --> 01:11:00,556
-You didn't even use the meat.
-No, it's over here.

1974
01:11:00,623 --> 01:11:03,826
Is it in the onion?
And you're putting it on the sauce.

1975
01:11:03,892 --> 01:11:05,194
8. SPREAD THE SAUCE, TOP WITH THE ROLL

1976
01:11:06,528 --> 01:11:07,896
AND FOR THE FINISHING TOUCH?

1977
01:11:08,631 --> 01:11:10,165
JULIENNING GREEN ONION

1978
01:11:11,100 --> 01:11:12,401
AND DROPPING IT IN OIL!

1979
01:11:12,468 --> 01:11:15,771
8. DEEP-FRY JULIENNED GREEN ONION
AND TOP THE STRIP LOIN AND ONION ROLL

1980
01:11:15,838 --> 01:11:17,506
That looks good.

1981
01:11:17,573 --> 01:11:19,541
VENUS CLAM

1982
01:11:19,608 --> 01:11:20,542
VENUS CLAM

1983
01:11:20,609 --> 01:11:21,443
VENUS CLAM

1984
01:11:22,778 --> 01:11:24,446
PLATING THE SECOND DISH!

1985
01:11:24,513 --> 01:11:27,349
FIRST, THE CHINESE-STYLE
STIR-FRIED BOK CHOY

1986
01:11:27,850 --> 01:11:32,087
10. LAY OUT STIR-FRIED BOK CHOY
AND TOP WITH ORANGE

1987
01:11:32,154 --> 01:11:33,355
FOUR-CHEESE

1988
01:11:33,422 --> 01:11:35,524
The problem is that radish.

1989
01:11:36,525 --> 01:11:38,727
ANOTHER LAYER OF BRAISED RIBS AND CHEESE

1990
01:11:38,794 --> 01:11:41,430
10. FILL THE RADISH
WITH LAYERS OF RIB MEAT AND CHEESE

1991
01:11:42,131 --> 01:11:43,632
Is he not putting it in the oven?

1992
01:11:44,233 --> 01:11:45,100
That would make it delicious.

1993
01:11:45,167 --> 01:11:46,502
It should. No?

1994
01:11:46,568 --> 01:11:48,871
Did it seem that urgent?
He's finally starting to talk.

1995
01:11:48,937 --> 01:11:51,607
-"Will he put it in the oven?"
-I'm so curious.

1996
01:11:52,508 --> 01:11:53,609
It'll taste better after it's baked.

1997
01:11:53,676 --> 01:11:55,577
Does he have time to do that?

1998
01:11:55,644 --> 01:11:57,246
May I use your oven, Chef Sam?

1999
01:11:57,313 --> 01:11:58,814
Go ahead.

2000
01:11:58,881 --> 01:12:01,116
Wait, why is the oven off?

2001
01:12:01,183 --> 01:12:02,885
It's an emergency!

2002
01:12:02,951 --> 01:12:03,919
Wait.

2003
01:12:03,986 --> 01:12:06,555
-Use a torch.
-Just use the microwave option.

2004
01:12:06,622 --> 01:12:08,657
-Use a torch.
-You don't have much time.

2005
01:12:08,724 --> 01:12:10,559
-The microwave.
-You don't have time.

2006
01:12:10,626 --> 01:12:12,361
-You have it on your side.
-Whatever's on.

2007
01:12:12,428 --> 01:12:14,563
Yes, he's using the microwave option.

2008
01:12:14,630 --> 01:12:16,131
Oriental dressing?

2009
01:12:16,198 --> 01:12:17,366
He's just like me.

2010
01:12:17,433 --> 01:12:18,767
LEMON ORIENTAL DRESSING

2011
01:12:18,834 --> 01:12:22,471
-You have under a minute!
-Under one minute!

2012
01:12:23,339 --> 01:12:24,773
I hope this gets ready.

2013
01:12:24,840 --> 01:12:26,041
BOK CHOY, LEMON ORIENTAL DRESSING!

2014
01:12:26,442 --> 01:12:28,777
I'd love to give them
just two more minutes.

2015
01:12:28,844 --> 01:12:30,979
-It's way too tight, right?
-Yes.

2016
01:12:31,847 --> 01:12:33,682
Sung-jun looks busy!

2017
01:12:33,749 --> 01:12:35,951
Wait, I'm running out of time.

2018
01:12:36,018 --> 01:12:37,920
One minute left! Sung-jun faces a crisis!

2019
01:12:37,986 --> 01:12:39,254
Spin it around!

2020
01:12:39,321 --> 01:12:40,589
SECRETLY TRYING TO BE COOL

2021
01:12:41,890 --> 01:12:42,858
GOOD!

2022
01:12:43,425 --> 01:12:45,527
Sung-jun, you don't have anything ready.

2023
01:12:45,594 --> 01:12:46,862
-That looks good.
-Oh, no.

2024
01:12:46,929 --> 01:12:49,465
I wonder what that sauce
in the piping bag will be like.

2025
01:12:49,531 --> 01:12:51,433
Wait, is he only serving the fruit salad?

2026
01:12:52,835 --> 01:12:54,503
Will she only get to eat the fruit salad?

2027
01:12:54,570 --> 01:12:56,572
-No.
-She can eat Sam's main dish

2028
01:12:56,638 --> 01:12:58,207
and finish with Sung-jun's dessert.

2029
01:12:58,273 --> 01:12:59,908
Thirty seconds.

2030
01:12:59,975 --> 01:13:02,211
11. TOP STIR-FRIED BOK CHOY
WITH STIR-FRIED SEAFOOD

2031
01:13:02,277 --> 01:13:04,613
-It looks like Chef Sam is almost done.
-Yes.

2032
01:13:04,680 --> 01:13:05,914
He's now plating the dish.

2033
01:13:05,981 --> 01:13:07,282
She won't eat just the salad.

2034
01:13:07,349 --> 01:13:08,751
You don't have much time.

2035
01:13:08,817 --> 01:13:10,352
11. TOP WITH STRAWBERRY,
PEANUT CREAM CHEESE

2036
01:13:11,587 --> 01:13:13,722
SALAD MIX

2037
01:13:13,789 --> 01:13:14,890
-This is it.
-Two dishes?

2038
01:13:14,957 --> 01:13:16,992
Fifteen seconds.

2039
01:13:17,526 --> 01:13:19,061
SUNG-JUN FEELS RUSHED!

2040
01:13:19,128 --> 01:13:20,529
-Basil!
-Ten seconds.

2041
01:13:20,596 --> 01:13:22,030
Did you miss anything? Ten seconds.

2042
01:13:22,097 --> 01:13:24,333
Nine. Eight. Seven.

2043
01:13:24,400 --> 01:13:25,968
-Six. Five.
-Sam finishes.

2044
01:13:26,635 --> 01:13:27,536
CLAP

2045
01:13:28,170 --> 01:13:29,671
SLIDES

2046
01:13:29,738 --> 01:13:30,773
Sam finishes.

2047
01:13:30,839 --> 01:13:32,474
-That's hot. Be careful.
-Be careful.

2048
01:13:32,541 --> 01:13:34,510
-With your bare hands?
-Bare hands?

2049
01:13:34,576 --> 01:13:35,711
The chef who doesn't feel heat.

2050
01:13:35,778 --> 01:13:37,579
-One.
-Ring the bell.

2051
01:13:38,614 --> 01:13:40,816
-Yes, Sung-jun finishes too.
-No olive oil on top?

2052
01:13:40,883 --> 01:13:41,717
Wow.

2053
01:13:41,784 --> 01:13:43,952
-It's okay.
-Sam made three dishes?

2054
01:13:44,787 --> 01:13:45,988
This is amazing.

2055
01:13:47,289 --> 01:13:50,459
-Sam has changed.
-He has.

2056
01:13:50,526 --> 01:13:51,860
Has he been taking cooking lessons?

2057
01:13:51,927 --> 01:13:53,929
SAM LIVES SO DILIGENTLY

2058
01:13:53,996 --> 01:13:57,499
All dishes were made just for Nana.

2059
01:13:57,566 --> 01:14:00,569
She asked the chefs
to use up her mother's ingredients.

2060
01:14:00,636 --> 01:14:03,806
Please try Chef Sam's dishes first.

2061
01:14:04,373 --> 01:14:09,411
THREE-COLORED SEAFOOD SALAD

2062
01:14:10,312 --> 01:14:14,917
AN ONION BLOSSOM WITH MEAT

2063
01:14:15,417 --> 01:14:19,621
CHEF SAM KIM'S MAGIC PIZZA? HAH!

2064
01:14:20,456 --> 01:14:22,458
-He made three dishes.
-My gosh.

2065
01:14:23,392 --> 01:14:26,962
-Nana does not take any dishes lightly.
-No.

2066
01:14:27,029 --> 01:14:28,897
You'll see the seafood salad.

2067
01:14:28,964 --> 01:14:30,799
Sprinkle some lemon juice on the salad,

2068
01:14:30,866 --> 01:14:34,303
then add the salad mix on top.

2069
01:14:35,971 --> 01:14:37,539
-The salad mix goes on top?
-On the top?

2070
01:14:37,606 --> 01:14:39,374
He basically made two dishes.

2071
01:14:39,441 --> 01:14:41,109
You could've just topped it for her.

2072
01:14:41,176 --> 01:14:43,145
But it's not as beautiful
when it's on the salad.

2073
01:14:43,212 --> 01:14:44,813
-The presentation?
-That's why.

2074
01:14:44,880 --> 01:14:48,250
-It's the presentation too.
-It's also visually charming.

2075
01:14:48,317 --> 01:14:51,320
Then try it with the orange
and a piece of seafood you like

2076
01:14:51,386 --> 01:14:53,288
with a spoon.

2077
01:14:53,355 --> 01:14:56,091
-She also likes seafood.
-I do.

2078
01:14:56,158 --> 01:14:59,895
It feels like this won't make me fat
no matter how much I eat it.

2079
01:14:59,962 --> 01:15:01,129
It looks good.

2080
01:15:01,196 --> 01:15:04,833
I wonder what the refreshing flavor
is like with some seafood.

2081
01:15:04,900 --> 01:15:05,968
GASP

2082
01:15:06,034 --> 01:15:07,202
MMM

2083
01:15:08,670 --> 01:15:11,340
It's tough to read her face.

2084
01:15:11,907 --> 01:15:13,542
She's savoring the flavor.

2085
01:15:13,609 --> 01:15:14,877
It's a bit…

2086
01:15:14,943 --> 01:15:16,144
What is it?

2087
01:15:16,712 --> 01:15:17,646
First of all,

2088
01:15:18,447 --> 01:15:20,482
-it tastes smoky.
-Smoky.

2089
01:15:20,549 --> 01:15:24,920
The smoky flavor of the seafood
hits really strong.

2090
01:15:24,987 --> 01:15:27,623
These don't taste like seafood
that had been sitting in a freezer.

2091
01:15:27,689 --> 01:15:30,292
It tastes extremely fresh.

2092
01:15:30,359 --> 01:15:32,494
Is it as if he used fresh seafood?

2093
01:15:32,561 --> 01:15:34,796
IMMEDIATELY TAKES ANOTHER BITE

2094
01:15:37,566 --> 01:15:40,202
-It's also quite refreshing.
-Refreshing?

2095
01:15:40,269 --> 01:15:43,105
I think it's because of the orange.

2096
01:15:43,171 --> 01:15:45,207
The freshness of the orange

2097
01:15:45,274 --> 01:15:47,676
makes the salad even lighter.

2098
01:15:47,743 --> 01:15:49,578
Did you put it in
because she's Orange Caramel?

2099
01:15:49,645 --> 01:15:50,646
That's right.

2100
01:15:50,712 --> 01:15:51,747
CANINE OF DESIRE

2101
01:15:51,813 --> 01:15:52,915
Hah!

2102
01:15:52,981 --> 01:15:54,216
Hah!

2103
01:15:54,283 --> 01:15:55,317
How shameless.

2104
01:15:55,384 --> 01:15:58,554
-Hui-tae has changed.
-My gosh.

2105
01:15:58,620 --> 01:16:00,055
The seafood tastes smoky

2106
01:16:00,122 --> 01:16:02,090
because I burnt the garlic on purpose.

2107
01:16:02,157 --> 01:16:03,892
<i>-Oh, garlic.</i>
<i>-It was intentional.</i>

2108
01:16:03,959 --> 01:16:06,161
The burnt garlic flavor
adds a nice touch to seafood.

2109
01:16:07,062 --> 01:16:10,299
This is a salad, but it feels
more like an actual main dish.

2110
01:16:10,365 --> 01:16:11,266
That's right.

2111
01:16:11,333 --> 01:16:13,201
Why don't you try the next one?

2112
01:16:13,869 --> 01:16:16,772
-This one.
-That was the salad. Now, the main dish.

2113
01:16:16,838 --> 01:16:19,841
Cut it in half, and eat the onion
and the meat with the sauce.

2114
01:16:19,908 --> 01:16:22,477
Cut it in half
and eat it with the balsamic sauce.

2115
01:16:22,544 --> 01:16:24,179
There's mango at the bottom.

2116
01:16:24,246 --> 01:16:26,348
<i>I diced mango and onion</i>
<i>into the sauce.</i>

2117
01:16:26,415 --> 01:16:28,584
<i>-You diced it?</i>
<i>-In the sauce?</i>

2118
01:16:28,650 --> 01:16:30,352
SMELLS IT FIRST

2119
01:16:31,620 --> 01:16:32,955
It smells like dumplings.

2120
01:16:33,021 --> 01:16:34,156
It smells like dumplings?

2121
01:16:35,290 --> 01:16:36,592
Did he use dumpling fillings?

2122
01:16:37,225 --> 01:16:38,894
SURPRISED

2123
01:16:39,361 --> 01:16:40,762
It must be good.

2124
01:16:40,829 --> 01:16:43,532
-The onion must be sweet.
-When I eat salads,

2125
01:16:43,599 --> 01:16:45,968
I often eat it with balsamic sauce.

2126
01:16:46,034 --> 01:16:50,606
But I've never had the sauce
taste this oily before.

2127
01:16:51,406 --> 01:16:52,240
Do you not like that?

2128
01:16:52,307 --> 01:16:54,142
-It's so good.
-It's good?

2129
01:16:54,209 --> 01:16:58,814
Also, the sourness of the diced mangoes

2130
01:16:58,880 --> 01:17:01,583
refreshes my mouth very quickly.

2131
01:17:01,650 --> 01:17:03,685
Also, the onion

2132
01:17:03,752 --> 01:17:06,888
tastes much sweeter than usual.

2133
01:17:06,955 --> 01:17:08,757
DEEP-FRYING MADE IT EVEN SWEETER

2134
01:17:08,824 --> 01:17:10,859
This salad was refreshing,

2135
01:17:10,926 --> 01:17:13,629
and this main dish tastes very rich.

2136
01:17:13,695 --> 01:17:15,163
REFRESHING SALAD
AND RICH BEEF ONION ROLL

2137
01:17:15,230 --> 01:17:17,432
The harmony is wonderful.

2138
01:17:17,499 --> 01:17:18,734
THE OPPOSITES' PERFECT HARMONY

2139
01:17:18,800 --> 01:17:21,837
Next, please try Chef Sung-jun's dish.

2140
01:17:21,903 --> 01:17:22,871
<i>Magic Pizza.</i>

2141
01:17:22,938 --> 01:17:25,107
REFRESHING MACEDONIA

2142
01:17:25,173 --> 01:17:28,644
AND CHICAGO PIZZA
REINTERPRETED WITH RADISH

2143
01:17:29,144 --> 01:17:32,581
CHEF KWON SUNG-JUN'S MAGIC PIZZA

2144
01:17:32,648 --> 01:17:35,384
-How do I eat this?
-Is the radish cooked?

2145
01:17:36,084 --> 01:17:38,620
Please try the Macedonia first.

2146
01:17:38,687 --> 01:17:41,456
-Macedonia, the fruit salad.
-This comes first?

2147
01:17:41,523 --> 01:17:43,925
-You'll see cream in the middle.
-Yes.

2148
01:17:43,992 --> 01:17:46,094
You can eat that part with the strawberry.

2149
01:17:46,161 --> 01:17:48,163
-With the strawberry?
-At once?

2150
01:17:48,230 --> 01:17:49,898
Yes, one spoonful at a time.

2151
01:17:49,965 --> 01:17:54,636
It would've been better
if the fruit salad didn't seem as dry.

2152
01:17:54,703 --> 01:17:56,938
-I guess that's how you do it in Italy.
-It's not Macedonia

2153
01:17:57,005 --> 01:17:59,141
-if it has too much juice.
-It must be good.

2154
01:17:59,708 --> 01:18:02,878
What do I call this on the top?
This cream.

2155
01:18:02,944 --> 01:18:04,579
-Yes, the cream. Peanut cream.
-The sauce?

2156
01:18:04,646 --> 01:18:07,883
<i>I mixed peanut butter</i>
<i>with apple cinnamon jam.</i>

2157
01:18:07,949 --> 01:18:09,284
It sounds so good.

2158
01:18:09,351 --> 01:18:12,888
It seeps into my mouth very lightly,

2159
01:18:12,954 --> 01:18:15,957
but it maintained a strong peanut scent.

2160
01:18:16,024 --> 01:18:20,896
The balance of sweetness
and sourness is perfect.

2161
01:18:20,962 --> 01:18:22,597
Does the cream help a lot?

2162
01:18:22,664 --> 01:18:24,666
-Totally.
-The peanut cream?

2163
01:18:24,733 --> 01:18:26,802
-Yes.
-It brings the ingredients together.

2164
01:18:26,868 --> 01:18:29,538
It feels like a cake you can eat
with a spoon.

2165
01:18:29,604 --> 01:18:30,639
Pound cake?

2166
01:18:30,706 --> 01:18:32,808
-A cake you eat with a spoon.
-A cake you eat with a spoon.

2167
01:18:32,874 --> 01:18:34,609
-It's like that. Yes.
-Ones like tiramisu.

2168
01:18:34,676 --> 01:18:36,478
What's important is this pizza.

2169
01:18:36,545 --> 01:18:38,213
Yes, that pizza is the main dish.

2170
01:18:38,280 --> 01:18:39,414
Chicago pizza.

2171
01:18:39,481 --> 01:18:42,317
-Is it cooked?
-Everyone was impressed with the idea.

2172
01:18:42,384 --> 01:18:44,586
-He used radish.
-Radish as the dough.

2173
01:18:44,653 --> 01:18:46,988
First, cut it into bite-sized pieces.

2174
01:18:47,055 --> 01:18:50,358
Then try everything together,
meat, cheese, and radish.

2175
01:18:50,425 --> 01:18:51,526
Cut the radish too.

2176
01:18:51,593 --> 01:18:53,061
BEGINS TO CUT

2177
01:18:53,128 --> 01:18:55,997
-I hope the cheese is runny.
-Oh, no.

2178
01:18:56,064 --> 01:18:58,567
-Goodness.
-It needed more time in the oven.

2179
01:18:58,633 --> 01:19:01,169
-It probably hardened.
-It feels like a dish for meat and cheese.

2180
01:19:01,236 --> 01:19:04,139
-But it seems soft to the cut.
-Yes, it's soft. I think it's cooked.

2181
01:19:04,206 --> 01:19:06,441
-Try everything together.
-That's the dough.

2182
01:19:06,508 --> 01:19:07,876
Can you see the cross section?

2183
01:19:07,943 --> 01:19:10,612
-Does she eat the radish too?
-The cross section.

2184
01:19:10,679 --> 01:19:12,614
That's the cross section.

2185
01:19:12,681 --> 01:19:14,716
Please try lots of meat and cheese.

2186
01:19:14,783 --> 01:19:17,119
-Okay.
-Lots of meat and cheese.

2187
01:19:17,853 --> 01:19:19,721
I can eat this when I'm on a diet, right?

2188
01:19:19,788 --> 01:19:20,756
Of course.

2189
01:19:21,389 --> 01:19:22,557
It doesn't have any carbs.

2190
01:19:22,624 --> 01:19:24,226
YUM

2191
01:19:24,292 --> 01:19:27,195
The dough wasn't made with flour,
but radish.

2192
01:19:28,830 --> 01:19:29,698
MMM!

2193
01:19:29,765 --> 01:19:32,968
-I wonder if the radish will work.
-Right?

2194
01:19:33,034 --> 01:19:36,037
She probably has never had
anything like this.

2195
01:19:36,605 --> 01:19:39,174
The taste of cheese is the strongest.

2196
01:19:39,241 --> 01:19:40,342
The filling

2197
01:19:40,408 --> 01:19:42,944
tastes like braised short ribs.

2198
01:19:43,011 --> 01:19:46,181
<i>-That's where he got the meat.</i>
<i>-He put braised short ribs inside.</i>

2199
01:19:46,248 --> 01:19:47,949
He used that to make Chicago pizza.

2200
01:19:48,016 --> 01:19:49,417
-Braised ribs with cheese.
-Braised ribs with cheese.

2201
01:19:49,484 --> 01:19:51,553
-Braised ribs with cheese.
-Braised ribs with cheese.

2202
01:19:51,620 --> 01:19:52,754
Yes, that's it.

2203
01:19:52,821 --> 01:19:53,855
You even used radish.

2204
01:19:53,922 --> 01:19:55,690
Didn't you say this was a pizza?

2205
01:19:55,757 --> 01:19:57,859
Braised short ribs were my m…

2206
01:19:57,926 --> 01:19:59,561
-My motif.
-You called it a pizza.

2207
01:19:59,628 --> 01:20:03,365
-The radish is important.
-Personally, I love radishes so much.

2208
01:20:03,431 --> 01:20:06,134
So I'm enjoying
this texture and sweetness.

2209
01:20:06,201 --> 01:20:07,469
-Is it okay?
-It goes well.

2210
01:20:07,536 --> 01:20:09,938
So has it been cooked thoroughly?

2211
01:20:10,005 --> 01:20:11,973
-Yes, it's completely cooked.
-It is?

2212
01:20:12,040 --> 01:20:14,042
But it's not too soft

2213
01:20:14,109 --> 01:20:15,277
that it'll fall apart.

2214
01:20:15,343 --> 01:20:17,445
It has a bit of bite to it.

2215
01:20:17,512 --> 01:20:18,914
Al dente.

2216
01:20:18,980 --> 01:20:20,081
SO IT WAS INTENTIONAL

2217
01:20:20,148 --> 01:20:21,850
He's saying it was intentional.

2218
01:20:21,917 --> 01:20:24,119
-It was cooked to al dente.
-That's Italy.

2219
01:20:24,186 --> 01:20:26,555
-He's becoming shameless too.
-It was his intention.

2220
01:20:28,957 --> 01:20:30,592
It's very tasty.

2221
01:20:30,659 --> 01:20:32,561
-That's what's important.
-Yes.

2222
01:20:32,627 --> 01:20:34,996
Then Kyuhyun, will you try some?

2223
01:20:35,063 --> 01:20:36,665
-Yes, please.
-You should try some.

2224
01:20:37,232 --> 01:20:39,935
-That's the seafood salad.
-Yes.

2225
01:20:41,203 --> 01:20:43,939
TRYING THE SEAFOOD SALAD FIRST

2226
01:20:44,906 --> 01:20:47,242
That looked good. It looks so good.

2227
01:20:48,310 --> 01:20:49,978
GLARING

2228
01:20:50,045 --> 01:20:51,947
DOES THAT MEAN HE LIKES IT?

2229
01:20:52,013 --> 01:20:54,850
The sauce coats the seafood completely

2230
01:20:54,916 --> 01:20:56,685
with its stickiness.

2231
01:20:57,252 --> 01:20:59,254
It feels like I'm chewing on the sea.

2232
01:20:59,321 --> 01:21:00,488
I love it.

2233
01:21:00,555 --> 01:21:02,357
-Like he's chewing on the sea.
-The sea.

2234
01:21:02,424 --> 01:21:03,692
It's light and delicious.

2235
01:21:03,758 --> 01:21:05,727
Now, the main dish.

2236
01:21:05,794 --> 01:21:08,997
He's trying a bite
with onion, meat, and everything.

2237
01:21:10,398 --> 01:21:12,200
Will it please Kyuhyun's palate too?

2238
01:21:15,103 --> 01:21:17,138
This main dish has the best harmony.

2239
01:21:17,205 --> 01:21:20,375
<i>The onion and the meat filling.</i>

2240
01:21:20,442 --> 01:21:21,476
The balsamic sauce is insane.

2241
01:21:22,110 --> 01:21:23,011
Thank you.

2242
01:21:23,545 --> 01:21:25,413
Next, Chef Sung-jun's dishes.

2243
01:21:25,480 --> 01:21:26,414
STARTING WITH THE MACEDONIA

2244
01:21:30,652 --> 01:21:34,022
The dishes don't seem like much,
but you both look so happy.

2245
01:21:34,089 --> 01:21:36,091
-Is it the cream?
-The cream.

2246
01:21:36,157 --> 01:21:37,392
PEANUT CREAM CHEESE
WOW

2247
01:21:37,459 --> 01:21:38,693
PROUD

2248
01:21:38,760 --> 01:21:40,629
It's like the cream you'll find

2249
01:21:40,695 --> 01:21:43,331
<i>on top of a very delicious piece of cake.</i>

2250
01:21:43,398 --> 01:21:46,034
Like you're only eating
the delicious part on top?

2251
01:21:46,101 --> 01:21:47,235
Yes, something like that.

2252
01:21:47,636 --> 01:21:49,537
THE TASTING ALWAYS ENDS WITH NAM-NO

2253
01:21:49,604 --> 01:21:51,339
-It holds everything together.
-The cream.

2254
01:21:51,406 --> 01:21:53,808
The flavor of peanut sauce

2255
01:21:53,875 --> 01:21:57,078
comes alive and becomes richer
when it's hydrated.

2256
01:21:57,145 --> 01:22:00,582
The fruit in the salad
will give out juice as you chew on it,

2257
01:22:00,649 --> 01:22:02,584
so it probably amplifies
the flavor of the sauce.

2258
01:22:02,651 --> 01:22:04,386
That's Chef Kim Poong.

2259
01:22:04,452 --> 01:22:06,421
This was so moving.

2260
01:22:06,488 --> 01:22:07,789
He says it was moving.

2261
01:22:07,856 --> 01:22:08,957
How will you choose one?

2262
01:22:10,859 --> 01:22:13,695
The Macedonia was so delicious.

2263
01:22:13,762 --> 01:22:17,832
I'm sure people who like radish
will like this one.

2264
01:22:22,037 --> 01:22:23,638
That's radish-cago pizza.

2265
01:22:27,242 --> 01:22:28,209
EYES SHUT

2266
01:22:28,276 --> 01:22:30,879
It's taking him a while
to chew on the radish.

2267
01:22:30,946 --> 01:22:32,647
-It's an emergency.
-It's al dente.

2268
01:22:32,714 --> 01:22:33,848
Looks like he has a toothache.

2269
01:22:33,915 --> 01:22:35,350
I didn't expect it to be so firm.

2270
01:22:37,519 --> 01:22:39,154
THE LIGHT GOES ON

2271
01:22:39,220 --> 01:22:40,221
It's an emergency!

2272
01:22:40,288 --> 01:22:42,090
Nana had small pieces after cutting it.

2273
01:22:42,157 --> 01:22:44,159
-It may vary depending on the spot.
-But Kyuhyun

2274
01:22:44,225 --> 01:22:46,227
-had a big piece.
-Cut it into smaller pieces.

2275
01:22:46,294 --> 01:22:47,329
It's good too,

2276
01:22:47,395 --> 01:22:50,131
but it would've been better
if he had a little more time.

2277
01:22:50,732 --> 01:22:53,001
It would've been nice
if the cheese flowed out.

2278
01:22:53,068 --> 01:22:54,336
It was a mistake, Sung-jun.

2279
01:22:54,402 --> 01:22:55,403
My mistake.

2280
01:22:55,470 --> 01:22:58,340
-But Nana will choose the winner.
-Yes.

2281
01:22:58,406 --> 01:23:00,175
<i>Press one for Sung-jun</i>

2282
01:23:00,875 --> 01:23:02,577
<i>and two for Sam.</i>

2283
01:23:03,445 --> 01:23:06,047
Make your decision and press the button.

2284
01:23:08,450 --> 01:23:10,185
-I did.
-She chose one.

2285
01:23:10,251 --> 01:23:13,722
Who did Nana choose?

2286
01:23:13,788 --> 01:23:15,623
-Let's find out!
-Let's find out!

2287
01:23:15,690 --> 01:23:17,993
They both cooked
with her mother's ingredients.

2288
01:23:18,059 --> 01:23:21,396
Will Sam take the star?

2289
01:23:21,463 --> 01:23:23,665
Or will it be Sung-jun?

2290
01:23:23,732 --> 01:23:25,133
-Gosh.
-Nana's choice!

2291
01:23:25,200 --> 01:23:26,234
Which one is it?

2292
01:23:27,102 --> 01:23:28,603
Mom's ingredients!

2293
01:23:29,170 --> 01:23:30,038
Who's the winner?

2294
01:23:30,105 --> 01:23:31,339
Who's the winner?

2295
01:23:31,806 --> 01:23:33,408
SAM KIM WINS

2296
01:23:33,875 --> 01:23:34,743
MAGIC PIZZA? HAH! WINS

2297
01:23:34,809 --> 01:23:35,710
Sam Kim wins.

2298
01:23:35,777 --> 01:23:37,912
NANA CHOOSES SAM KIM!

2299
01:23:37,979 --> 01:23:40,448
-Chef Sam has been on fire.
-He's on fire.

2300
01:23:40,515 --> 01:23:42,784
I thought Chef Sam

2301
01:23:42,851 --> 01:23:46,554
had made two different dishes

2302
01:23:46,621 --> 01:23:50,358
that were of a higher quality
when it came to complete dishes.

2303
01:23:50,425 --> 01:23:52,293
Also, everything I tried

2304
01:23:52,360 --> 01:23:57,399
<i>tasted so healthy that I felt like</i>
<i>I could eat as much as I wanted.</i>

2305
01:23:57,465 --> 01:23:59,034
I loved that.

2306
01:23:59,100 --> 01:24:00,535
BOWING

2307
01:24:00,602 --> 01:24:02,804
Sam's rise is intimidating.

2308
01:24:02,871 --> 01:24:04,072
He now has four stars.

2309
01:24:05,373 --> 01:24:07,275
-Please put the star on him!
-Is he my new master?

2310
01:24:08,443 --> 01:24:10,512
This is Sam's fourth win.

2311
01:24:10,578 --> 01:24:13,181
-Do I put this here?
-He quickly takes the lead!

2312
01:24:13,248 --> 01:24:15,016
Congratulations, Sam!

2313
01:24:16,684 --> 01:24:18,520
I want to be here as a guest too.

2314
01:24:18,920 --> 01:24:19,888
A MAN WITH ABSOLUTE TASTE

2315
01:24:19,954 --> 01:24:21,156
VISITS CHEF & MY FRIDGE

2316
01:24:21,222 --> 01:24:22,524
This is insane.

2317
01:24:22,590 --> 01:24:24,893
Kyuhyun is an excellent cook.

2318
01:24:24,959 --> 01:24:26,795
He has a total of six fridges.

2319
01:24:26,861 --> 01:24:28,963
He was offered a spot
on <i>Culinary Class Wars!</i>

2320
01:24:29,030 --> 01:24:29,998
Are you serious?

2321
01:24:30,065 --> 01:24:31,466
<i>We prepared a blind test.</i>

2322
01:24:31,533 --> 01:24:32,867
It'll be insane if he gets this.

2323
01:24:32,934 --> 01:24:34,069
This is probably…

2324
01:24:34,135 --> 01:24:35,637
Wait, could this be…

2325
01:24:35,703 --> 01:24:38,506
-This is insanity!
-How did you get this right?

2326
01:24:38,573 --> 01:24:41,042
The best couple now faces one another.

2327
01:24:41,109 --> 01:24:42,510
He has never won against Poong.

2328
01:24:42,577 --> 01:24:44,079
He probably has a secret weapon.

2329
01:24:44,145 --> 01:24:45,613
I'll share the recipe if you pick me.

2330
01:24:45,680 --> 01:24:47,148
I've never seen him tout like this.

2331
01:24:47,215 --> 01:24:48,216
What's wrong?

2332
01:24:48,283 --> 01:24:49,451
HIS DIABOLICAL WRECKAGE DINING

2333
01:24:49,517 --> 01:24:50,485
-What?
-What's that?

2334
01:24:50,552 --> 01:24:52,654
-What is that?
-It smells like <i>jwibullori</i>.

2335
01:24:52,720 --> 01:24:54,656
<i>It's been a year</i>
<i>since he stood before the counter.</i>

2336
01:24:54,722 --> 01:24:56,458
<i>I'm not too nervous today.</i>

2337
01:24:56,524 --> 01:24:58,026
First, mash the salmon roe.

2338
01:24:58,093 --> 01:24:59,394
HE EVEN ADDS COMMENTS?

2339
01:24:59,461 --> 01:25:01,863
I prepared something to eat on the side.

2340
01:25:01,930 --> 01:25:03,331
I'VE NEVER SEEN KANG-ROK LIKE THIS

2341
01:25:03,398 --> 01:25:04,499
I'm making the dough.

2342
01:25:04,566 --> 01:25:06,367
For the dough, you'll use potato starch.

2343
01:25:06,434 --> 01:25:08,436
THE COMMENTARY BATTLE IS ON FIRE

2344
01:25:08,503 --> 01:25:09,637
What's it like?

2345
01:25:09,704 --> 01:25:10,538
Wow.

2346
01:25:10,605 --> 01:25:12,140
I want to have him as my master.

2347
01:25:17,078 --> 01:25:18,880
Is this how I do it?

2348
01:25:18,947 --> 01:25:20,348
RE-ADAPTATION COMPLETE

2349
01:25:30,258 --> 01:25:35,029
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
